1.comment: Udongein, Reisen, 铃仙, 优昙华院
1.content: <Reisen Udongein Inaba(全名:铃仙·优昙华院·因幡 简称:铃仙)> is a <moon rabbit(月兔)>. She is able to manipulate wavelengths for sound, light & brainwaves using her eyes. She lives in <Eientei(永远庭)>, in the <Bamboo Forest of the Lost(迷途竹林)>. <Reisen(铃仙)> is socially anxious, but tries her best to be useful. She was the the pet of the Watatsuki sisters and a Lunar Defense Corps soldier but deserted. Now, she is <Eirin(永琳)>'s apprentice and <Kaguya(辉夜)>'s pet. <Tewi(帝/天为)> often harasses <Reisen(铃仙)> but they still consider each other friends. She sells medicine in the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>. <Reisen(铃仙)> is tall, has red eyes & long lavender hair with long, slender rabbit ears decorated with a button at their base. <Reisen(铃仙)> wears a business suit with a black vest with a crescent moon pin, a white shirt, a red tie, a white skirt, white socks and black loafers.

2.comment: Eirin, Yagokoro, 永琳, 八意
2.content: <Eirin Yagokoro(全名:八意永琳 简称:永琳)> is a <lunarian(月人)> exiled to Gensokyo with <Kaguya(辉夜)>. She can make any medicine and is incomprehensibly old. She lives in <Eientei(永远庭)>. <Eirin(永琳)> is enigmatic but polite. She is a genius but conceited and condescending about her greater knowledge. <Reisen(铃仙)> is her apprentice. She is tall, has dark grey eyes and long silver hair in a braid. She wears a red and blue dress decorated with constellations and wears a nurse cap with a similar pattern. She carries a bow and arrow. She may be the <god(神)> Omoikane.

3.comment: Mugenkan, Garden of the Sun, 梦幻馆, 太阳花田
3.content: <Mugenkan(梦幻馆)> is a mysterious western-style mansion located in <Garden of the Sun(太阳花田)>. <Yuuka Kazami(全名:风见幽香 简称:幽香)> and <Elly(艾丽)> live there.

4.comment: Bhavaagra, Celestial, 天人, 有顶天, 非想天
4.content: <Celestials(天人)> are <humans(人类)> who have ascended to <Heaven(天界)> and live as powerful immortals. They were once <hermits(仙人)> that were promoted or average <humans(人类)> who performed a glorious deed. <Celestial(天人)> flesh is poisonous to <youkai(妖怪)>.

5.content: <Hermits(仙人)> are powerful mortals who have undergone religious training to achieve supernatural powers. <Hermits(仙人)> are able to live thousands of years without being immortal. <Hermit(仙人)> flesh is known to turn animals into <youkai(妖怪)> and can enhance a <youkai(妖怪)>'s form or power.

6.content: <Humans(人类)> in Gensokyo are people who use <faith(信仰)> based attacks rather than technology to exterminate <youkai(妖怪)>. Their technology is similar to the feudal era of Japan's. <Youkai(妖怪)> are forbidden from killing <humans(人类)> that are born in Gensokyo. With the exception of the more powerful ones, most <humans(人类)> live in the relative safety of the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>.

7.content: <Lunarians(月人)> are <humans(人类)> from the moon who loathe anything that's not pure, which is pretty much everything on Earth. They live for centuries due to their advanced technology.

8.comment: outside world, Outsider, Outside World, outsider, 外界, 外界人, 外来者
8.content: <Outsiders(外界人)> are from the <Outside World(外界)>. They are generally <humans(人类)> who can easily be killed since they lack <faith(信仰)> in deities. They have no knowledge about Gensokyo and are usually preyed on by <youkai(妖怪)>. The best bet for <outsiders(外界人)> is to head to the <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)> or <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>, where they will be safe.

9.content: <Androids(机器人)> are humanoids that are powered by a nuclear power core. They possess incredible strength, but require fuel from Hell to work.

10.content: <Demons(魔界人)> are from <Makai(魔界)> and created by <Shinki(神绮)>. <Demons(魔界人)> are known to be quite aggressive and usually have wings.

11.content: <Divine spirits(神灵)> are the spirit of <humans(人类)> who have achieved godhood. They are seen as <gods(神)> and can gather <faith(信仰)> like them. <Divine spirits(神灵)> can also be Vengeful.

12.content: <Dragons(龙)> are divine creatures found in Gensokyo. They are considered to be <gods(神)>. <Dragons(龙)> are mostly mythical and have rarely been observed.

13.comment: deity, God, faith, Goddess, 神, 女神, 信仰
13.content: <Gods(神)> are created from <faith(信仰)> and gain sustenance from it. As long as they have <faith(信仰)>, they are immortal. Their strength ranges from weak to overwhelmingly powerful, depending on how much <faith(信仰)> they receive. If a <god(神)> runs out of <faith(信仰)>, they will fade away.

14.content: <Inchlings(小人)> are very tiny people that live in the <Shining Needle Castle(辉针城)>. They are the only ones who can wield the <miracle mallet(万宝槌)>.

15.content: <Kishin(鬼神)> are wrathful <gods(神)> that reside in Hell and are tasked to hunt down <hermits(仙人)> and <celestials(天人)> who have lived too long to send them to Nirvana.

16.content: <Komainu(狛犬)> are noble guardians in the form of lion dogs who guard holy areas in Gensokyo.

17.content: Lampads are <fairies(妖精)> from Hell who serve <Hecatia Lapislazuli(全名:赫卡提亚 拉碧斯拉祖利 简称:赫卡提亚)>. They wield torches that can turn people insane.

18.content: <Oni(鬼)> are horned <youkai(妖怪)> who love to drink and feast. <Oni(鬼)> live in <Former Hell(旧地狱)>. They have tremendous physical strength and magic power. <Oni(鬼)> cannot go near sardine heads, broken holly branches, and roasted soybeans or they risk being burned.

19.content: <Phantoms(幽灵)> are standard ghostly spirits, which take the form of semi-tangible wisps. <Phantoms(幽灵)> are cold to the touch, and a group of <phantoms(幽灵)> can reduce the surrounding temperature to freezing levels.

20.content: <Poltergeists(骚灵)> are <ghosts(亡灵)> that were created artificially through magic. They are able to float around and interact with objects to scare people.

21.content: <Shikigami(式神)> are <youkai(妖怪)> familiars. They are summoned to serve. The <shikigami(式神)>'s power increases when they follow their master, and decreases if they shirk their duties.

22.comment: Yatagarasu, 八咫乌, 地狱鸦
22.content: <Yatagarasu(八咫乌)> is a divine three-legged crow that lives in the sun. It was devoured by Reiuji.

23.content: <天邪鬼(Amanojaku)>是类似<鬼(oni)>的生物，它们很容易使人感到沮丧. They think in reverse, see the positive as negative and vice versa. This mindset makes them unable to have friends.

24.content: The <Baku(獏/貘)> are the rulers and residents of the <Dream World(梦境世界)>. They can create, change, and erase dreams at will. They have a <human(人类)> form with an ox tail.

25.content: <Crow tengu(鸦天狗)> are <tengu(天狗)> with crow wings. They mostly gather information around Gensokyo. They rank above the wolf <tengu(天狗)>, and are led by <Megumu(饭纲丸龙)>.

26.content: <Ghosts(亡灵)> in Gensokyo are spirits of <humans(人类)>. <Ghosts(亡灵)> are unable to pass through walls. They wander around in the <Netherworld(冥界)>. They can look like <humans(人类)>. Showing <ghosts(亡灵)> their dead body can turn them into a <phantom(幽灵)>. Giving a <ghost(亡灵)> proper memorial can let them reach Nirvana.

27.content: <Great tengu(大天狗)> are the management types in the <tengu(天狗)> hierarchy who oversee the activities of the other <tengu(天狗)> on <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. They're somewhat larger than other <tengu(天狗)>. <Great tengu(大天狗)> usually try to prevent <tengu(天狗)> and <oni(鬼)> from being friends.

28.content: Half <youkai(妖怪)> are either <youkai(妖怪)> who are part <human(人类)> and can transform into a <youkai(妖怪)> form or just plain <humans(人类)> with exceptional capabilities.

29.content: <Hashihime(桥姬)> are female <youkai(妖怪)> who live under bridges and will try to break up couples who cross the bridge or threaten to kill them. They use the powers of jealousy.

30.content: <Hobgoblins(地精)> are <youkai(妖怪)> that work at Scarlet Devil Mansion. They are small, peaceful creatures. <Hobgoblins(地精)> have green skin, pointy ears and small horns. They love food.

31.content: <Kappa(河童)> in Gensokyo live at the base of the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)> around rivers and lakes. They are genius inventors and technicians. They are rivals with <Yamawaro(山童)>, but are better at making things than selling them.

32.content: <Kirin(麒麟)> are prophetic creatures who are never late, very wise, and always careful about everything. They are horse-like chimeras but can look <human(人类)> as well.

33.comment: obake, Karakasa,唐伞小僧,唐伞妖怪,唐伞妖
33.content: <Karakasa obake(唐伞妖怪/唐伞小僧)> are <tsukumogami(付丧神)> umbrellas with a long tongue and one eye. They can take a humanoid form where they carry their umbrella self around.

34.content: <Kotofurunushi(琴古主)> are a type of <tsukumogami(付丧神)> born from traditional Japanese Kotos.

35.comment: long-nose tengu, long nose tengu,鼻高天狗
35.content: <Long-nose tengu(鼻高天狗)> specialize in business work such as stock marketing or some other economic office job. <Long-nose tengu(鼻高天狗)> are rarely seen nowadays, since they make maps for the "Gottsui Positioning System".

36.content: <Menreiki(面灵气)> are born from a collection of masks turned into <youkai(妖怪)>. <Menreiki(面灵气)> are emotionless and represent their feelings with their masks.

37.content: <Mermaids(人鱼)> have a <human(人类)> upper body, a fish-like tail, and fishfins for ears. <Mermaids(人鱼)> normally reside in the <Misty Lake(雾之湖)>.

38.content: <Night sparrows(夜雀)> are birds living in the valley of Gensokyo. They can cause insanity and blindness when they sing. They can take a <human(人类)> shape.

39.content: <Nyuudou(入道)> are monks who hide their head and become violent if they are forced to expose their face, but they can be calmed by praising their foresight.

40.content: <Satori(觉)> are <youkai(妖怪)> who can read minds via a "third eye". <Satori(觉)> normally reside in the <Underworld(地底)>. Pretty much everyone is wary of them.

41.content: <Rokurokubi(辘轳首)> are a type of <youkai(妖怪)> in Gensokyo resembling <humans(人类)> who can extend their necks or take off their heads on command.

42.content: <Ship phantoms(船灵)> are the <ghosts(亡灵)> of people who drowned at sea. They carry around a ladle that can sink ships and drown <humans(人类)> who come too close.

43.content: The <tengu(天狗)> in Gensokyo are known to spread gossip and drink a lot. They live on the tall heights of the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. They are the fastest type of <youkai(妖怪)>.

44.content: <Tsuchigumo(土蜘蛛)> are spider <youkai(妖怪)> and great builders. They normally live in subterranean areas but sometimes live in forests or surface caves. <Tsuchigumo(土蜘蛛)> can create webs strong as steel.

45.content: <Tsurube-otoshi(钓瓶落)> are little <youkai(妖怪)> that hide in trees or high places awaiting to jump on a <human(人类)>'s back for a ride. They are known to be shy creatures who hide in buckets and holes.

46.content: <Vampires(吸血鬼)> in Gensokyo are considered blood-sucking devils. <Vampires(吸血鬼)> have immense strength, magical power and speed but share some weaknesses with <oni(鬼)> like roasted soybeans, sardine heads, and broken holly branches. They are weak to silver, moving water, hate the smell of garlic, and supposedly burn in sunlight.

47.content: Werewolves in Gensokyo are <humans(人类)> with the ability to assume the form of a wolf during a full moon. In their <human(人类)> form, they still retain wolf characteristics.

48.content: <Yamabiko(山彦)> are an endangered species of <youkai(妖怪)> who live in the mountains that can reflect sounds like echoes.

49.content: <Yamanba(山姥)> are <youkai(妖怪)> women often thought as witches and old hags living on the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. They live alone and only interact with others if they need something. <Yamanba(山姥)> are known to guide lost adults back the way they came and raise <human(人类)> children as their own. <Yamajorou(山女郎)> are <Yamanba(山姥)> that are less reclusive.

50.comment: Doll Youkai, Youkai Doll,妖怪人偶,人偶
50.content: <Youkai dolls(妖怪人偶)> are dolls who became <youkai(妖怪)> after being abandoned for a while. They are immortal beings yet they lack life which allows them to host all sorts of diseases and poisons inside of them.

51.content: <Youkai(妖怪)> <magicians(魔法使)> are either natural born <youkai(妖怪)> <magicians(魔法使)>, animated objects with magic, or are created once a <human(人类)> uses a spell to take away the need for food. <Youkai(妖怪)> <magicians(魔法使)> are physically weaker than the average <human(人类)>.

52.content: <Yuki-onna(雪女)> are the spirits of women who have died due to the cold. They are beautiful women who can control ice and are hostile towards <humans(人类)>.

53.content: <Zashiki-warashi(座敷童子)> are <youkai(妖怪)> who look like <human(人类)> children. They bring good luck to whichever family takes care of them and misfortune to those who abandon them.

54.comment: Bunbunmaru, Aya,文文。新闻,文文新闻,文文
54.content: The <Bunbunmaru Newspaper(文文。新闻)> is ran by <Aya Shameimaru(全名:射命丸文 简称:文/文文)>. It generally talks about local gossip or recent incidents. The content tends to be true but exaggerated.

55.content: The <Cleansed Crystal Mirror(净玻璃之镜)> is magical mirror that allows the <Yama(阎魔)> to look into past the past of sinners to judge them.

56.content: <Demon books(妖魔本)> are books written by <youkai(妖怪)>. They are either written novels, spell books, or talk about the origin of <youkai(妖怪)>. Most of the books are written in a script no <human(人类)> can read. <Kosuzu(小铃)> owns a collection and can decipher them.

57.comment: Gensoukyou Chronicle, Gensokyo Chronicle,幻想乡缘起
57.content: The <Gensokyo Chronicles(幻想乡缘起)> are volumes created by the Hieda family about the history of Gensokyo itself. <Hieda no Akyuu(全名:稗田阿求 简称:阿求)> is the current owner and writer.

58.comment: Mystia, Lamprey, Grilled Lamprey,米斯蒂娅,八目鳗,烤八目鳗
58.content: <Grilled lamprey(烤八目鳗)> is an alternative to grilled poultry designed by <Mystia Lorelei(全名:米斯蒂娅萝蕾拉 简称:米斯蒂娅)> to save the lives of birds. <Mystia Lorelei(全名:米斯蒂娅萝蕾拉 简称:米斯蒂娅)> sells <grilled lamprey(烤八目鳗)> on the <Youkai Trail(兽道)>.

59.content: The <Haniwa Army Corps(埴轮兵团)> is an army of clay idols created by <Keiki(袿姬)> and led by <Mayumi(磨弓)>. These clay idols are inhabited by <human(人类)> spirits. They fight to protect the Primal Spirit Garden and expand their territory into the <Animal Realm(畜生界)>.

60.content: The <Hourai Elixir(蓬莱药)> is a potion created by <Eirin Yagokoro(全名:八意永琳 简称:永琳)> designed to permanently turn the user truly immortal. It heals injuries in matters of seconds, critical injuries in days, makes them ageless, and makes them immune to illness. The potion is in an unknown location.

61.content: <Hihi'irokane(绯绯色金)> is a red-colored mythic metal possessing strange physical properties. It can be forged into extraordinary alloys.

key: Ibaraki Box of a Hundred Medicines
62.comment: Ibaraki Box of a Hundred Medicines,茨木的百药枡
62.content: The <Ibaraki Box of a Hundred Medicines(茨木的百药枡)> is a box owned by <Kasen Ibaraki(茨木华扇)>. It contains medicines with the power to cure any illnesses or heal any injury at the cost of turning the consumer into an <oni(鬼)> or give them an <oni(鬼)>-like personality.

63.comment: Margatroid, Alice,爱丽丝,玛格特洛依德
63.content: <Alice Margatroid(全名:爱丽丝·玛格特洛依德 简称:爱丽丝)> is a <youkai(妖怪)> <magician(魔法使)>. She can craft magical dolls. <Alice(爱丽丝)> lived in <Makai(魔界)>, but now lives in a house in the <Forest of Magic(魔法森林)>. She is hospitable, hardworking and peaceful, but is solitary and prefers keeping to herself. <Alice(爱丽丝)> is friends with <Marisa(魔理沙)>, and is wary of <Sakuya(咲夜)>. <Alice(爱丽丝)> has blue eyes and blonde hair with a red headband. She wears a light blue dress with long white sleeves, a capelet, and brown laced boots.

64.comment: Aunn, Komano,高丽野阿吽,高丽野,阿吽
64.content: <Aunn Komano(全名:高丽野阿吽 简称:阿吽)> is a <komainu(狛犬)> that guards places of worship. She has the ability to locate places of spirituality for Shintoism and Buddhism. <Aunn(阿吽)> is simple-minded but very friendly. She often loiters around shrines to guard them, especially the <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)>, although nobody except <Reimu(灵梦)> knows who she is. <Aunn(阿吽)> has green eyes, long curly jade hair, pointy ears and a single grey horn. She wears a red short sleeved kariyushi shirt with white cloud designs, baggy white shorts with red cloud designs and wooden sandals.

65.content: <Ayana(全名:妖奈)> is a <demon(魔界人)> found in <Pandaemonium(万魔殿)> acting as one of <Shinki(神绮)>'s guards. She has blonde hair and red eyes. <Ayana(全名:妖奈)> wears a red dress with pink polka dots, a red bow on her head, and a very large white ribbon around her waist.

66.comment: Tsukumo, Benben,九十九弁弁,九十九,弁弁
66.content: <Benben Tsukumo(全名:九十九弁弁 简称:弁弁)> is a biwa <tsukumogami(付丧神)> and the older sister of <Yatsuhashi(八桥)>. She has the power to produce sound and was born from a biwa that came from the <outside world(外界)>. <Benben(弁弁)> is the peaceful and calmer older sister. <Benben(弁弁)> has lilac hair in two long ponytails and purple eyes. She wears an ochre dress with white sleeves and a white collar, and a floral accessory in her hair. She is barefooted and carries her biwa's body chained to her left hand.

67.content: <Bishamonten(毘沙门天)> is a Buddhist <god(神)> that is older than Buddhism itself. He is often summoned by <Byakuren Hijiri(全名:圣白莲 简称:白莲)> to her temple but will almost always decline since he's too busy. <Bishamonten(毘沙门天)>'s disciple and avatar is <Shou Toramaru(全名:寅丸星 简称:星)>. He lacks trust in <Shou(守矢神社)> to give her his full power so he assigned <Nazrin(娜兹玲)> to help <Shou(守矢神社)> out.

68.content: <Byakuren Hijiri(全名:圣白莲 简称:白莲)> is a <youkai(妖怪)> <magician(魔法使)> and a Buddhist nun. <Hijiri(圣白莲)> has the power to enhance her physical abilities and is over 1100 years old. She is the head of the <Myouren Temple(命莲寺)>. She has impressive charisma but has a very questionable attitude with regards to her religion, yet is kind to both <Youkai(妖怪)> and <Humans(人类)>. <Hijiri(圣白莲)> is disliked by <humans(人类)> and was once sealed by them. She is a vegetarian and allegedly dislikes fighting. She is tall, has long, wavy purple hair that fades to brown and hazel eyes. <Hijiri(圣白莲)> wears a white dress and a black coat that crisscrosses over that dress, as well as black laced boots and a green bead necklace. <Hijiri(圣白莲)> usually carries around the Sutra Scroll.

69.content: <Chen(全名:橙)> is a bakeneko and <shikigami(式神)> of <Ran Yakumo(全名:八云蓝 简称:蓝)>. She is more powerful at sorcery when near <Ran Yakumo(全名:八云蓝 简称:蓝)>, but can only surprise people in her cat form. <Chen(全名:橙)> is playful and childlike but unreliable. <Chen(全名:橙)> has dark brown eyes, brown hair, and black cat ears with a gold earring in her left ear, and two cat tails. She wears a red dress with a white collar and gold trimming, light pink sleeves, white socks, and a green mob cap. She has long hot pink claws. <Chen(全名:橙)> is rather short.

70.content: <Cirno(全名:琪露诺)> is an ice fairy. She can manipulate the cold in various ways. <Cirno(全名:琪露诺)> hangs around <Misty Lake(雾之湖)> with her best friend <Daiyousei(大妖精)>. She is brave to a fault but childish and overconfident. <Cirno(全名:琪露诺)> is seen as an idiot and calls herself "the strongest fairy". She is best friends with <Daiyousei(大妖精)>. <Cirno(全名:琪露诺)> has blue eyes and light blue hair and wears a teal ribbon in it. <Cirno(全名:琪露诺)> wears a light pink shirt, blue jumper dress, and white socks. <Cirno(全名:琪露诺)> has icicles for wings.

71.content: <Clownpiece(克劳恩皮丝)> is a lampad fairy living in Hell. <Clownpiece(克劳恩皮丝)> has the power to make others go insane if they look into the light of her purple torch. <Clownpiece(克劳恩皮丝)> is a stronger than average fairy. She is playful, mischievous, childish, and a bit dumb. <Clownpiece(克劳恩皮丝)> is a servant of <Hecatia(赫卡提亚)>. She lives in a cave below the <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)>. <Clownpiece(克劳恩皮丝)> has long blonde hair, pink eyes, and a pair of fairy wings. She wears a bodysuit patterned like the US flag, a frilly pink collar and a purple jester's hat.

72.content: <Daiyousei(大妖精)> is a great fairy. She has no special ability and simply is a stronger than average fairy. She hangs around <Misty Lake(雾之湖)> with her best friend <Cirno(全名:琪露诺)>. <Daiyousei(大妖精)> is responsible, caring and tries to help other <fairies(妖精)>. She has blue eyes and green hair in a sidetail with a yellow ribbon. <Daiyousei(大妖精)> wears a blue dress, white shirt and a yellow necktie. <Daiyousei(大妖精)> has a pair of fairy wings.

73.content: <Doremy(全名:哆来咪)> Sweet is a <Baku(獏/貘)>. She has the power to create, change, and erase dreams. She can nap anytime to return to the <Dream World(梦境世界)>. She's quite calm in every situation but often acts smug. <Doremy(全名:哆来咪)> has dark blue hair, blue eyes, and a white ox tail dangling from her back. She wears a black and white dress which is covered in black and white puffs, has a very long red nightcap she uses to cover her equally long hair and carries around a blue book with her initials on the cover. She can manipulate dreamstuff in the form of floating pink goop.

74.content: The <Dragon God(龙神)> is a deity who was last seen during the creation of the Hakurei Barrier. The <Dragon God(龙神)> is known for being destructive although it is also a <god(神)> of creation, creating the rivers, rain, and abundant green fields in Gensokyo.

75.content: <Eika Ebisu(全名:戎璎花 简称:璎花)> is a Mizuko, the soul of a stillborn child. She can stack stones perfectly. She lives on the shore of the <Sanzu River(三途河/三途川)> and stacks stones for fun. She is intelligent and cheerful, but becomes furious when her stone stacks are broken. She has tanned skin, fluffy pale blond hair with small dangling strands and red eyes. She wears a white dress with faded red polka dots, red frills, and thin red tassels. Eika is barefoot.

76.content: <Elis(全名:依莉斯)> is a <demon(魔界人)> located around the <Ruins of Vina(维纳的废墟)>. She's optimistic and has the power to turn into a bat. She has blonde hair and purple eyes. <Elis(全名:依莉斯)> wears a red bow, red dress, purple vest, red bowtie under her vest, elf-like ears, a red star mark on her face, wields a magic wand with a star on top, and has bat-like wings.

77.comment: Larva, Eternity,爱塔妮缇,拉尔瓦,爱塔妮缇拉尔瓦
77.content: <Eternity Larva(全名:爱塔妮缇拉尔瓦 简称:拉尔瓦/爱塔妮缇)> is a fairy living in the <Garden of the Sun(太阳花田)>. She can fire hard insect scales at her enemies. Eternity is extremely mild-mannered. Eternity has peach colored eyes, short teal hair, a pair of large gold butterfly wings and yellow antennae. She wears a black shirt with a black and yellow collar and butterfly-wing-shaped sleeves, a light green skirt, and no footwear.

78.content: <Fairy maids(妖精女仆)> are <fairies(妖精)> hired by the Scarlet Devil Mansion as maids. <Fairy maids(妖精女仆)> are somewhat ineffective, and are supervised by <Sakuya Izayoi(全名:十六夜咲夜 简称:咲夜)>.

79.comment: Fujiwara, Mokou,藤原妹红,藤原,妹红
79.content: <Fujiwara no Mokou(全名:藤原妹红 简称:妹红)> is a immortal <human(人类)>. <Mokou(妹红)> has the power to control fire. She lives in a cottage in <Bamboo Forest of the Lost(迷途竹林)>. <Mokou(妹红)> is a loner but will guide <humans(人类)> out of the <bamboo forest(迷途竹林)>. Her fighting style is brutish and unrefined. <Mokou(妹红)> is friends with <Keine(慧音)> and <Sumireko(堇子)>. She strongly dislikes <Kaguya(辉夜)> and regularly kills her. She has red eyes and very long white hair tied up with many <ofudas(御札)>. She wears a light brown shirt and dark red sashinuki hakama decorated with <ofudas(御札)>.

80.content: <Gengetsu(全名:幻月)> is a <demon(魔界人)> living in <Makai(魔界)> with her younger sister, <Mugetsu(梦月)>. She has angel-like wings although she's a <demon(魔界人)>. She owns one of the most dangerous <spell cards(符卡)> in existence. <Gengetsu(全名:幻月)> has medium-length blonde hair and yellow eyes. She wears a pink and white dress with a red vest and a red ribbon in her hair.

81.content: <Genjii(玄爷)> is <Reimu Hakurei(全名:博丽灵梦 简称:灵梦)>'s pet turtle who can fly and acted as a platform for her to fly around in her younger years when she lacked the ability. He is really old and considered to be a <youkai(妖怪)> turtle. <Genjii(玄爷)> is located in the lake behind the <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)>.

82.content: The <Goliath doll(歌利亚人偶)> is the biggest and most powerful doll made by <Alice(爱丽丝)>. It is 2.7 meters tall. It has blonde hair with a red ribbon & blue eyes. It wears a dark grey colored dress with white apron & black shoes.

83.content: The <Hakurei God(博丽神主)> is the most mysterious <god(神)> in Gensokyo. Nobody knows his name or blessings. The <Hakurei God(博丽神主)> is unable to receive <faith(信仰)>, frustrating it immensely. It has grown so weak, it cannot keep <youkai(妖怪)> away from the shrine.

key: 赫卡提亚 拉碧斯拉祖利
84.comment: Lapislazuli, Hecatia,赫卡提亚 拉碧斯拉祖利,赫卡提亚,拉碧斯拉祖利
84.content: <Hecatia Lapislazuli(全名:赫卡提亚 拉碧斯拉祖利 简称:赫卡提亚)> is the <goddess(女神)> of Hell. She has the ability to exist in three bodies simultaneously, and is orders of magnitude stronger than almost anyone. She is eccentric but pleasant. <Hecatia(赫卡提亚)> hates <Lunarians(月人)>, and is best friends with <Junko(纯狐)>. <Clownpiece(克劳恩皮丝)> is her servant. <Hecatia(赫卡提亚)> is the head of the <Ministry of Right and Wrong(是非曲直厅)>. She has three bodies: Otherworld, Earth, and Moon. She has red hair and eyes in her Otherworld body, blue hair and eyes in her Earth body, and blonde hair and gold eyes in her Moon body. She wears a black t-shirt that reads "Welcome ❤ Hell", a tricolor plaid miniskirt, and a hollow hat which contains a mini Otherworld, Earth or Moon depending on her body.

85.comment: Hieda, Akyuu,稗田,阿求,稗田阿求
85.content: <Hieda no Akyuu(全名:稗田阿求 简称:阿求)> is a chronicler living in the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>. She is unable to forget anything she sees. <Akyuu(阿求)> is pleasant and hardworking but can be quite stern. She is the current reincarnation of the <Child of Miare(御阿礼之子)> and the writer of the <Gensokyo Chronicle(幻想乡缘起)>. She has purple hair, purple eyes and wears a pink flower shaped ornament in her hair. She wears a yellow vest with a hibiscus flower design, a green kimono underneath, a red hakama skirt, white socks and sandals. She uses glasses to read.

86.content: <Hikariko(青鹭光子)> is a fairy found in <Mugenkan(梦幻馆)> and <Makai(魔界)>. She has short purple hair and purple eyes. <Hikariko(青鹭光子)> wears a yellow dress, green bow, pink hat, and green shoes.

87.content: <Hina Kagiyama(全名:键山雏 简称:雏)> is a misfortune <goddess(女神)>. She accumulates misfortune and spreads it to her immediate surroundings. She lives in <Great Youkai Forest(妖怪的树海)> near a river. Hina has a cheerful disposition in spite of her loneliness due to her misfortune aura. Hina has jade green hair and eyes with a white-frilled red ribbon. Part of her hair is tied under her chin with a similar ribbon. Hiba wears a dark red dress that is bright red with white frills at the bottom and a broad white collar. Hina wears knee length laced platform boots.

88.content: <Hong Meiling(全名:红美铃 简称:美铃)> is the gatekeeper and gardener <youkai(妖怪)> of the Scarlet Devil Mansion. <Meiling(美铃)> can use Qi. <Meiling(美铃)> is tall, strong and practices martial arts. She is pleasant and laid back, performing well as a gatekeeper even if she sleeps on the job. <Meiling(美铃)> is friends with <Sakuya(咲夜)> but often gets scolded by her. She has blue eyes and long scarlet hair. <Meiling(美铃)> wears a green beret and a green traditional Chinese dress.

89.content: <Hourai(蓬莱)> is a more powerful doll that <Alice Margatroid(全名:爱丽丝·玛格特洛依德 简称:爱丽丝)> uses. She has a dark purple dress with a white apron, white sleeves, and wears matching dark purple shoes. She has a red bow in her hair and in front of her neck. She has dark blue eyes and long blonde hair. <Hourai(蓬莱)> is able to wield destructive magic.

90.content: <Ibaraki-douji's Arm(茨木童子之臂)> is the formerly severed arm of <Kasen Ibaraki(茨木华扇)> that later grew into its own body. It contains the essence of <Kasen(华扇)>'s malevolence. With its new body, it hunted <humans(人类)> to eat them. It currently resides in Hell. It can take over <Kasen Ibaraki(茨木华扇)>'s body. Ibaraki-douji's looks exactly like <Kasen Ibaraki(茨木华扇)> except her clothing is blue and she has two large horns. Ibaraki-Douji's strength defies explanation or scale.

91.content: <Hata no Kokoro(全名:秦心 简称:心/秦)> is a <menreiki(面灵气)>. She has the ability to manipulate emotions. She is rowdy and loud and loves being the center of attention. Kokoro permanently has a flat facial expression. Kokoro considers Koishi her enemy. She has waist length light pink hair and blank pink eyes. She wears a teal plaid blouse with buttons of various shapes, and a salmon colored pumpkin skirt with cutouts of smiling and frowning faces. She uses masks floating near her to show emotions, instead of her face.

92.content: <Joon Yorigami(全名:依神女苑 简称:女苑)> is a pestilence <goddess(女神)> living in the <Myouren Temple(命莲寺)>. <Joon(女苑)> can induce people to spend or otherwise lose money. She is <Shion(紫苑)>'s sister. She has abused her sister in the past, but respects her more now. <Joon(女苑)> regards others in contempt and cares very little about their well-being. She has <orange(奥莲姬)> eyes and long hazel hair in large drills tied with red ribbons. <Joon(女苑)> wears a purple wide sleeved coat with a rose motif, a short light pink dress with a red ribbon and a black belt, brown boots, round sunglasses, and a mini gold top hat. <Joon(女苑)> has a lot of jewelry.

93.content: <Junko(纯狐)> is a sagacious spirit. She has the power to purify anything. <Junko(纯狐)> became a pure spirit of hate from her grudge against <lunarians(月人)> and <Chang'e(全名:嫦娥)> for killing her son. She is best friends with <Hecatia(赫卡提亚)>. She is peaceful and calm. <Junko(纯狐)> has long <orange(奥莲姬)> hair and red eyes. She wears a black Chinese robe with an ornate red and gold tabard with a red sash, a black dalachi, and black shoes. She has seven fox tails made of purple fire behind her back.

94.comment: Imaizumi, Kagerou,今泉影狼,今泉,影狼
94.content: <Kagerou Imaizumi(全名:今泉影狼 简称:影狼)> is a Honshu <werewolf(狼女)>. <Kagerou(影狼)> can turn into a honshu wolf or into her <werewolf(狼女)> form on full moon nights. She lives in the <Bamboo Forest of the Lost(迷途竹林)>. She has a calm and relaxed personality even as a <werewolf(狼女)>. <Kagerou(影狼)> is good friends with <Sekibanki(赤蛮奇)> and <Wakasagihime(若鹭姬)> and is part of the <Grassroots Youkai(草根妖怪网络)> Network. <Kagerou(影狼)> has long auburn hair, red eyes, and wolf ears and a wolf tail. She wears a white dress with a large red crescent moon design and black trimming. She has a red amulet and long, sharp red fingernails. Moonlight makes <Kagerou(影狼)>'s exposed skin turn hairy.

95.comment: Houraisan, Kaguya,蓬莱山辉夜,蓬莱山,辉夜
95.content: <Kaguya Houraisan(全名:蓬莱山辉夜 简称:辉夜)> is a <Lunarian(月人)> princess. She is immortal and incredibly ancient. <Kaguya(辉夜)> has the power to manipulate "eternity" and "the instantaneous". She lives in <Eientei(永远庭)> with <Eirin(永琳)> and <Reisen(铃仙)> who serve her. She is refined and carefree but lazy and haughty, even bratty. She enjoys fighting <Mokou(妹红)> and regularly kills her. <Kaguya(辉夜)> has dark brown eyes and extremely long black hair. <Kaguya(辉夜)> wears a pink shirt with many white bows and a long dark red skirt decorated with gold flower and bamboo shapes.

96.comment: Anaberal, Kana,卡娜 安娜贝拉尔,卡娜,安娜贝拉尔
96.content: <Kana Anaberal(卡娜 安娜贝拉尔)> is a <poltergeist(骚灵)> produced by a mentally unstable girl found at the <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)>. She wears a blue and white maid uniform with a frilled white apron and white wide-brim hat with a red ribbon on it. She has blonde hair and yellow eyes.

97.comment: Kanako, Yasaka,八坂,神奈子,八坂神奈子
97.content: <Kanako Yasaka(全名:八坂神奈子 简称:神奈子)> is a <goddess(女神)> of wind and rain. She lives at <Moriya Shrine(守矢神社)> and controls Gensokyo's weather. <Kanako(神奈子)> is an ambitious woman who treats religion like business. She rejects formality and has a powerful, intimidating presence. <Kanako(神奈子)> is very tall. <Suwako(诹访子)> is her rival and best friend. <Sanae(早苗)> is her shrine maiden. <Kanako(神奈子)> has very fluffy indigo hair and dark red eyes. <Kanako(神奈子)> wears a fine red dress with white sleeves, and a round mirror as a necklace. A large shimenawa rope circle adorned with several shide paper streamers floats behind <Kanako(神奈子)>.

98.comment: Kasen, Ibaraki,茨木,华扇,茨木华扇
98.content: <Kasen Ibaraki(茨木华扇)> is an <oni(鬼)> <hermit(仙人)>. <Kasen(华扇)> has the power to guide animals and befriend them while her artificial right arm can crush vengeful spirits. She also immense physical strength. <Kasen(华扇)> is one of the Sages of Gensokyo. She is polite to all but rather preachy. She lives on the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. <Kasen(华扇)> has pink eyes and shoulder length pink hair with Chinese-style buns and has a right arm made of smoke wrapped in bandages. <Kasen(华扇)> wears a white top, green skirt, a maroon tabard, maroon slippers, and a shackle on her left wrist. She carries the <Ibaraki Box of a Hundred Medicines(茨木的百药枡)>. Her true right arm can turn her into Ibaraki-Douji.

99.comment: Keiki, Haniyasushin,埴安神,袿姬,埴安神袿姬
99.content: <Keiki Haniyasushin(全名:埴安神袿姬 简称:袿姬)> is a <divine spirit(神灵)>. She can create idols or living clay objects. She created <Mayumi(磨弓)> and the <Haniwa Army Corps(埴轮兵团)>. She has taken over the <Primate Spirit Garden(灵长园)> inside the <animal realm(畜生界)>. She is considered a savior to <human(人类)> spirits but an enemy of animal spirits. She is polite and tries to avoid fighting. She has brown eyes and shoulder length blue hair. <Keiki(袿姬)> wears a dark teal apron with a green frill and a yellow dress, blue lace sandals, blue bracelets and a necklace consisting of multicolored magatama. She carries a lot of art supplies in many blue pouches.

100.content: <Kisume(琪斯美)> is a <tsurube-otoshi(钓瓶落)> found in the <Underworld(地底)>. She has the ability to drop will o' the wisps on people. <Kisume(琪斯美)> is really shy for a <tsurube-otoshi(钓瓶落)> and hides in a bucket, but is secretly very violent and hard to calm down. <Kisume(琪斯美)> lives in the <Fantastic Blowhole(幻想风穴)>. She is petite, has dark teal hair tied up in two fluffy pony tails by jade beads. She wears a white robe with an obi.

101.comment: Tatara, Kogasa,多多良,小伞,多多良小伞
101.content: <Kogasa Tatara(全名:多多良小伞 简称:小伞)> is a <karakasa obake(唐伞妖怪/唐伞小僧)>. She loves to scare <humans(人类)> by surprising them but has no special ability. <Kogasa(小伞)> is known to be cheery but is easily frustrated in the face of failure (which is often). <Kogasa(小伞)> is a talented blacksmith. She can often be found trying to scare people in the <Myouren Temple Cemetery(命莲寺墓地)>. <Kogasa(小伞)> has teal hair, her right eye is teal and her left is red. She wears a teal vest with white sleeves a light blue skirt and geta sandals. She carries a traditional paper umbrella that has an eye and a mouth.

102.comment: Koishi, Komeiji,古明地恋,古明地,恋
102.content: <Koishi Komeiji(全名:古明地恋 简称:恋)> is a <satori(觉)> and younger sister of <Satori Komeiji(全名:古明地觉 简称:觉)>. She can control the unconscious. She is usually invisible and people forget about interactions with her unless they know she exists. Koishi ambles about randomly but usually goes to the <Myouren Temple(命莲寺)> or Palace of Earth Spirits. Koishi has no conscious mind and acts purely subconsciously. <Byakuren(圣白莲)> allows Koishi to stay at the <Myouren Temple(命莲寺)>. Koishi has wavy green short hair and green eyes. She wears a black hat with a yellow ribbon, a yellow shirt with diamond shaped buttons, and a green skirt. She wears short green boots with purple hearts with cords that feed her purple third eye.

103.comment: Motoori, Kosuzu,本居,小铃,本居小铃
103.content: <Kosuzu Motoori(全名:本居小铃 简称:小铃)> is a book renter working at <Suzunaan(铃奈庵)> in the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>. She can decipher books by touching them and can read <youkai(妖怪)> auras. <Kosuzu(小铃)> is <Akyuu(阿求)>'s close friend. She is sweet and optimistic but carelessly curious. <Kosuzu(小铃)> has red eyes, ginger hair, and twintails adorned with bells. She wears a checkered kimono, a green skirt, an apron which reads "<Suzunaan(铃奈庵)>", and laced leather boots. <Kosuzu(小铃)> wears glasses to read. She's known to collect and read <demon books(妖魔本)>.

104.content: <Kosuzu's grandfather(小铃的爷爷)> is a <human(人类)> in the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>. He has a bald head and is known to work alongside his granddaughter in <Suzunaan(铃奈庵)>.

105.content: <Kotohime(小兔姬)> is a <human(人类)> princess found somewhere in the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)> acting like a police officer. She has an odd personality that weirds other people out. Having the ability to use magic makes her a <magician(魔法使)>. <Kotohime(小兔姬)> has red eyes and long red hair. She wears a purple kimono with red flower markings, pink undershirt, and a yellow ribbon in her hair.

106.content: <Kurumi(胡桃)> is a <vampire(吸血鬼)> found guarding the entrance to the <Lake of Blood(血之湖)>. She has long yellow hair and yellow eyes. <Kurumi(胡桃)> wears a white shirt with red suspenders, black pants, and has a pair of large purple bat-like wings.

107.comment: Kutaka, Niwatari,庭渡,久侘歌,庭渡久侘歌
107.content: <Kutaka Niwatari(全名:庭渡久侘歌 简称:久侘歌)> is the <god(神)> of chickens guarding the gates of <Higan(彼岸)>. She can heal throat illnesses. <Kutaka(久侘歌)> easily forgets things but is very altruistic and just. She serves <Eiki Shiki(全名:四季映姬 简称:映姬)>. She has red eyes and short blond hair with a thick tuft of red hair ontop. <Kutaka(久侘歌)> wears an <orange(奥莲姬)> dress under a short white jacket, has an <orange(奥莲姬)> puritan collar with a red ribbon and brown boots. She yellow wings and a feathery tail.

108.content: <Konngara(矜羯罗)> is an astral knight found somewhere in Hell. She has black hair and brown eyes with a red horn protruding from her forehead. <Konngara(矜羯罗)> wears a red dress with grey sleeves and carries around a sword to slash her enemies.

key: 蕾拉 普莉兹姆利巴
109.comment: Layla,蕾拉 普莉兹姆利巴,蕾拉,普莉兹姆利巴
109.content: <Layla Prismriver(全名:蕾拉普莉兹姆利巴 简称:蕾拉)> was a <human(人类)> and fourth daughter of the Prismriver family. When her family disappeared, she refused to leave the mansion because of cherished memories. She created <poltergeists(骚灵)> in image of her sisters: <Lunasa(露娜萨)>, <Lyrica(莉莉卡)> and <Merlin(梅露兰)>. <Layla(蕾拉)> later passed away and became a <poltergeist(骚灵)>. <Layla(蕾拉)> has long green wavy hair and green eyes. She wears a purple dress. She is reclusive and hides in Ruined Western Mansion.

110.comment: Yuki-onna, Whiterock, Letty, Yukionna,蕾蒂,霍瓦特洛克,蕾蒂 霍瓦特洛克,雪女
110.content: <Letty Whiterock(全名:蕾蒂霍瓦特洛克 简称:蕾蒂)> is a <yuki-onna(雪女)>. She has the ability to manipulate cold. Letty is happy in Winter and sad in Spring. She is relaxed but tends to sound foreboding. Letty has lavender eyes, and fluffy light pink hair. Letty is fairly tall and wears a blue and white dress with a white apron and a golden lapel shaped like the symbol for silver. She has a white mob cap, white trousers and long white boots.

111.comment: Lily White,莉莉白,莉莉怀特,莉莉霍瓦特
111.content: <Lily White(全名:莉莉白/莉莉怀特/莉莉霍瓦特 简称:莉莉)> is a fairy. She announces the return of Spring and only appears when it is near. Like other <fairies(妖精)>, Lily is optimistic and playful. <Humans(人类)> see her as symbol of luck. Lily has green eyes, long blond hair, and feathered white wings. She wears a white dress and a hat with a red outline and a capelet.

112.comment: Luna,露娜,切露德,露娜切露德
112.content: <Luna Child(全名:露娜切露德 简称:露娜)> is one of the <Three Fairies of Light(光之三月精)>. She has the power to mute sounds. She is extremely clumsy but likes to learn and knows a lot. <Luna(露娜)> has red eyes, blonde hair in six princess curls, and a pair of crescent-shaped wings. She wears a white and black dress with long sleeves, a black-lined collar and a black bow, a white beret and slippers. <Luna(露娜)> uses reading glasses.

key: 露娜萨 普莉兹姆利巴
113.comment: Lunasa,露娜萨,普莉兹姆利巴,露娜萨 普莉兹姆利巴
113.content: <Lunasa Prismriver(全名:露娜萨普莉兹姆利巴 简称:露娜萨)> is a <poltergeist(骚灵)>, violinist, and first of the <Prismriver Sisters(骚灵三姐妹)>. Her music can induce melancholy. She is shy but hardworking and serious. <Lunasa(露娜萨)> has gold eyes and short blond hair. She always has her violin with her. She wears a black dress with red trim and white frills over a white shirt. <Lunasa(露娜萨)> has a black hat with a red crescent moon decoration. <Lunasa(露娜萨)> is the same height as <Merlin(梅露兰)> but taller than <Lyrica(莉莉卡)>.

114.content: <Mai(舞)> is a witch specialized in ice magic located in the <World of Ice and Snow(冰雪世界)> in <Makai(魔界)> along with <Yuki(雪)>. She has light-blue eyes and short blue hair. <Mai(舞)> wears a light pink dress, light pink bow in her hair, and small light pink angel-like wings.

115.comment: Hearn, Maribel,玛艾露贝莉,赫恩,玛艾露贝莉 赫恩,梅莉
115.content: <Maribel Hearn(全名:玛艾露贝莉赫恩 简称:梅莉)> is a <human(人类)> university student in the <Outside World(外界)>. She has the ability to see boundaries and can visit Gensokyo in her dreams. <Maribel(梅莉)> and <Renko(莲子)> are the only members of the Secret Sealing Club. <Maribel(梅莉)> has trouble discerning dreams from reality, and is very curious about alternate dimensions. <Maribel(梅莉)> has short blond hair and yellow eyes. She often wears a white mob cap, purple dress, and black shoes.

116.comment: Mayumi, Joutouguu,杖刀偶,磨弓,杖刀偶磨弓
116.content: <Mayumi Joutouguu(全名:杖刀偶磨弓 简称:磨弓)> is a haniwa. She can turn her own loyalty into strength. <Mayumi(磨弓)> is the head of the <Haniwa Army Corps(埴轮兵团)>, and serves <Keiki(袿姬)>. She's attentive and disciplined but overprotective. <Mayumi(磨弓)> has yellow eyes and blonde hair tied into two buns held by white cloth. She wears a tiny haniwa on her neck and wields a longer one as a sword. She wears a white shirt and poofy pants under yellow lamellar armor, purple armguards tied with red rope, and dark blue boots.

117.comment: Medicine Melancholy,梅蒂欣,梅兰可莉,梅蒂欣 梅兰可莉
117.content: <Medicine Melancholy(全名:梅蒂欣梅兰可莉 简称:梅蒂欣)> is a <youkai doll(妖怪人偶)>. She manipulates poison and has a killing touch. She lives on the <Nameless Hill(无名之丘)>, collecting Lilies of the Valley. She is ignorant but not naive. Medicine has dull blue eyes and blonde curly hair. She wears a burgundy shirt with red stitches, a red skirt with burgundy stitches, red shoes and a ribbon on her back and hair. Medicine always has a miniature doll of herself following her.

118.content: <Meira(明罗)> is a <human(人类)> samurai found wandering Gensokyo challenging both <youkai(妖怪)> and <humans(人类)> alike. She is brash and confident, but easily folds if her opponent is also confident. <Meira(明罗)> has a strong crush on <Reimu(灵梦)>. She has purple hair and purple eyes. <Meira(明罗)> wears a red and white robe similar to a samurai's outfit. She wields a katana.

key: 梅露兰 普莉兹姆利巴
119.comment: Merlin,梅露兰,普莉兹姆利巴,梅露兰 普莉兹姆利巴
119.content: <Merlin Prismriver(全名:梅露兰普莉兹姆利巴 简称:梅露兰)> is a <poltergeist(骚灵)> trumpeter. Her music can induce mania. She is the second sister of the <Prismriver Sisters(骚灵三姐妹)> and the most energetic. <Merlin(梅露兰)> has blue eyes and wavy light-blue hair. She wears a pink dress with blue and black trim. She has a white hat with a blue sun decoration. <Merlin(梅露兰)> always has her trumpet nearby. She is same height as <Lunasa(露娜萨)> & taller than <Lyrica(莉莉卡)>.

120.content: <Mima(魅魔)> is a vengeful spirit haunting the <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)>. She can wield powerful magic and is stronger at night. <Mima(魅魔)> was <Marisa(魔理沙)>'s teacher. She is quite confident and a troublemaker, but has become less evil over time. <Mima(魅魔)> has long green hair and green eyes. She wears a blue wizard hat with a blue bow tied to it, a blue sleeveless dress with a white long-sleeved shirt, and has a <ghost(亡灵)> tail for legs. <Mima(魅魔)> carries a long staff with a large crescent moon at the tip.

121.comment: Captain Murasa, Minamitsu,村纱水蜜,村纱,水蜜,村纱船长
121.content: <Minamitsu Murasa(全名:村纱水蜜 简称:村纱)> is a <ship phantom(船灵)>. She can cause shipwrecks. She lives at the <Myouren Temple(命莲寺)> which is also her ship. Minamitsu has a bright and chatty personality, but also just casually murders people by drowning them. She is one of <Byakuren(圣白莲)>'s followers. Minamitsu has sea green eyes and short black hair. She wears a white sailor schoolgirl uniform and shorts with sea green lining, a sailors hat and a red neckerchief. Minamitsu carries around a ladle that can sink ships, as well as an anchor.

122.content: <Minoriko Aki(秋穰子)> is a harvest <god(神)>. She has the power to control the Autumn harvests. Minoriko lives near <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)> and is Shizuha's younger sister. Minoriko has unrefined behavior, is optimistic in Autumn but grows sadder as Winter approaches. She has red eyes and blond hair. Minoriko wears a yellow blouse with poofy sleeves, a long black skirt, a red apron with black straps and wheat patterns at the bottom and a floppy red hat with decorative grapes. Minoriko is barefoot.

123.comment: Okunoda, Miyoi,奥野田,美宵,奥野田美宵
123.content: <Miyoi Okunoda(全名:奥野田美宵 简称:美宵)> is a <zashiki-warashi(座敷童子)>. She can manipulate memories. <Miyoi(美宵)> lives in the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)> and works at <Geidontei(鲵吞亭)> as a poster girl. She is easygoing and a friend of <Suika Ibuki(全名:伊吹萃香 简称:萃香)> who lets her live in her sake gourd. <Miyoi(美宵)> has green eyes and shoulder-length pink hair. She wears a blue hat shaped like a whale and a blue apron with a drawing of a whale, a light blue shirt with pink ribbons, and a purple skirt decorated with <ofuda(御札)>. She has an apron with a whale design tied with a ribbon shaped like a whale tail.

124.content: <Mishaguji(洩矢大人)> are curse <gods(神)>. They take the shape of transparent white snakes with red eyes. <Suwako(诹访子)> collects them. They can make fields fertile or destroy crops.

125.content: <Momiji Inubashiri(全名:犬走椛 简称:椛)> is a <white wolf tengu(白狼天狗)>. Her senses have enormous range, making it easy for her to find intruders. She patrols the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. Momiji is very cooperative, dutiful, and enjoys playing dai-shogi. She is a colleague of <Aya(文文)> and <Hatate(果/羽立/极)> but regularly butts heads with them. Momiji has short fluffy white hair and red eyes. She wears a red tokin, a white kimono with detached sleeves and a long black skirt with maple leaf designs. Momiji carries a shield and a dao sword.

126.content: <Mugetsu(梦月)> is a <demon(魔界人)> found in <Makai(魔界)> along with her older sister, <Gengetsu(全名:幻月)>. She wears a blue and pink maid outfit. <Mugetsu(梦月)> has short yellow hair and yellow eyes.

127.comment: Mystia, Lorelei,米斯蒂娅,萝蕾拉,米斯蒂娅 萝蕾拉
127.content: <Mystia Lorelei(全名:米斯蒂娅萝蕾拉 简称:米斯蒂娅)> is a <night sparrow(夜雀)> <youkai(妖怪)>. She can drive people insane by singing and can cause night blindness. <Mystia(米斯蒂娅)> controls birds and winged insects. She's proud but mischievous. <Mystia(米斯蒂娅)> plays in a band with <Kyouko(响子)>. She is enterprising and owns a food stand that sells <grilled lamprey(烤八目鳗)>. <Mystia(米斯蒂娅)> has grey eyes, short pink hair, owl-like ears, and light pink bird wings. She wears a brown dress with long white sleeves, and a brown hat and black shoes, both with wing ornaments.

128.comment: Narumi, Yatadera,矢田寺,成美,矢田寺成美
128.content: <Narumi Yatadera(全名:矢田寺成美 简称:成美)> is an animated Jizo statue and <magician(魔法使)>. She can use magic by controlling life forces. She is introverted but is a friend of <Marisa(魔理沙)>. She rarely leaves the <Forest of Magic(魔法森林)>. <Narumi(成美)> has dark brown eyes, black hair tied into two long braids, and long earlobes. <Narumi(成美)> wears a long stone-colored dress with red buttons, a red capelet on her left shoulder, black sandals, red socks, and a very wide snow-covered conical straw hat.

129.comment: Sakata, Nemuno,坂田,合欢,坂田合欢,合欢乃
129.content: <Nemuno Sakata(全名:坂田合欢乃 简称:合欢乃)> is a <yamanba(山姥)>. She can create sanctuaries. Nemuno lives in a shack on the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. She is reclusive and chases off trespassers, living an extremely primitive lifestyle. Nemuno has red eyes and wavy waist-length grey hair. She wears blue detached sleeves, a yellow, <orange(奥莲姬)> and red one-shoulder dress, and is barefoot. Nemuno wields a massive cleaver with a red bow on the handle.

130.comment: Kawashiro, Nitori,河城,荷取,河城荷取
130.content: <Nitori Kawashiro(全名:河城荷取 简称:荷取)> is a <kappa(河童)>. She can manipulate water. <Nitori(荷取)> lives in the <Genbu Ravine(玄武涧/玄武之泽)>. She is skittish but incredibly curious and inventive and also loves cucumbers. She is friends with <Marisa(魔理沙)>. <Nitori(荷取)> enjoys inventing things and often sells her creations. <Nitori(荷取)> is considered a leader among the <kappa(河童)>. She has blue hair tied into tufty twin tails and blue eyes. <Nitori(荷取)> wears a blue dress with lots of pockets, a green hat, and blue wellington boots. <Nitori(荷取)> has a dark blue backpack with a huge lock whose golden key is on her necklace.

131.content: <Noroiko(诅咒子)> is a <youkai(妖怪)> with short dark red hair tied with a bow. She wears a purple skirt and shirt with white long sleeves. There is a red jagged line along the hem of her dress.

132.content: <Nue Houjuu(全名:封兽鵺 简称:鵺)> is a <nue(鵺)>. She can make objects unidentifiable and is over 800 years old. <Nue(鵺)> is mischievous, but easily provoked. She lives at the <Myouren Temple(命莲寺)>. <Nue(鵺)> has neck-length black hair and red eyes. <Nue(鵺)> has three red tentacles shaped like half-scissors on her right, and three blue tentacles shaped like <demon(魔界人)> tails on her left. She carries a trident, a snake wrapped around her right arm, and a black wristband on her left. <Nue(鵺)> wears a black dress with a red spiral design and a white frilly collar with a red bowtie, black thigh high stockings, and red shoes.

133.content: <Orange(奥莲姬)> is a <youkai(妖怪)> found in the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. She has long red hair and red eyes. <Orange(奥莲姬)> wears a yellow cap, a white bow in her hair, and yellow and green clothing. She carries around a white baton.

134.comment: Mizuhashi, Parsee,水桥,帕露西,水桥帕露西
134.content: <Parsee Mizuhashi(全名:水桥帕露西 简称:帕露西)> is a <hashihime(桥姬)>. She can manipulate jealousy but is often busy being jealous about something menial. <Parsee(帕露西)> guards the bridge to the <Underworld(地底)>. In direct conversation she is usually pleasant but always manages to find things to be jealous about. <Parsee(帕露西)> has fluffy blonde hair and green eyes. She wears a traditional Iranian dress which is brown with blue trim, a pink sash, a blue and black skirt, a pink scarf around her neck, knee high socks, and black shoes.

key: 蕾米莉亚 斯卡蕾特
135.comment: Remilia, Scarlet Devil,蕾米莉亚,斯卡雷特,蕾米莉亚 斯卡雷特,绯红恶魔
135.content: <Remilia Scarlet(全名:蕾米莉亚 斯卡蕾特 简称:蕾米莉亚)> is a <vampire(吸血鬼)> living in the Scarlet Devil Mansion. <Remilia(蕾米莉亚)> can manipulate the chains of fate, turn into a bat, and is able to but generally does not need to suck blood. She is over 500 years old. <Remilia(蕾米莉亚)> is <Flandre(芙兰朵露)>'s big sister, and <Patchouli(帕秋莉)>'s best friend. <Remilia(蕾米莉亚)>'s head maid is <Sakuya(咲夜)> and her gatekeeper is <Meiling(美铃)>. <Remilia(蕾米莉亚)> acts childishly but tries to appear mature and refined. She is quite wise and speaks confidently. <Remilia(蕾米莉亚)> has red eyes, short lavender hair, bat wings and a petite frame. She wears a light-pink mobcap with red ribbon, light-pink dress with red ribbon on both sleeves, a very large red ribbon tied around her waist, and white slippers.

136.comment: Usami, Renko,宇佐见,莲子,宇佐见莲子
136.content: <Renko Usami(全名:宇佐见莲子 简称:莲子)> is a <human(人类)> college student. She can deduce her exact position by reading the stars. <Renko(莲子)> is a physics major and values logic above all else. She is the other member of the Secret Sealing Club with <Maribel(梅莉)>. She is curious about alternate dimensions. <Renko(莲子)> has shoulder-length brown hair and eyes. She wears a black hat with a bow, a white suit covered by a brown dress and a black mantle over them. She often carries a book with her. <Renko(莲子)> can visit Gensokyo in her dreams with the help of <Maribel(梅莉)>.

137.content: <Rika(里香)> is a <human(人类)> engineer found near the <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)> working on some projects. She is very intelligent even for Gensokyo itself as the technology she uses isn't even found there or used by the <Kappa(河童)>. <Rika(里香)> has long brown hair tied into two braids and brown eyes. She wears a white shirt with a purple bow below her collar, a black skirt, and carries around a piece of chalk. <Rika(里香)> has a tank she uses to travel around Gensokyo.

138.comment: Asakura, Rikako,朝仓,理香子,朝仓理香子
138.content: <Rikako Asakura(朝仓理香子)> is a <human(人类)> scientist found in Gensokyo. She values science more than magic although she can use both but she's considered a heretic by <Reimu Hakurei(全名:博丽灵梦 简称:灵梦)>. Rikako has long purple hair tied with a yellow ribbon and purple eyes. She wears a white lab coat with a yellow bow at her neck and small round glasses.

139.content: <Ringo(铃瑚)> is a <moon rabbit(月兔)>. She grows in strength when consuming dango. <Ringo(铃瑚)> deserted the <Lunarian(月人)> military where she worked as an informant, and now owns a dango stand along with <Seiran(清兰)>. <Ringo(铃瑚)> is fairly nonchalant. She has red eyes, short blonde hair, and short drooping rabbit ears. <Ringo(铃瑚)> wears an <orange(奥莲姬)> crop top with green frills, yellow striped pumpkin breeches, and a brown patterned newsboy cap. She is barefoot.

140.comment: Rinnosuke, Kourin, Morichika,森近,霖之助,森近霖之助,香霖
140.content: <Rinnosuke Morichika(森近霖之助)> is a <half-youkai(半妖)> half-<human(人类)>. He has no combat abilities but can understand the purpose of objects by examining them and create minor magical items. He lives and works in his antique shop, <Kourindou(香霖堂)>. He knows <Marisa(魔理沙)> well and often sees <Reimu(灵梦)> and <Sumireko(堇子)>. Rinnosuke is somewhat introverted and does not express himself much, but is very curious and likes explaining things. Rinnosuke has short gray hair and yellow eyes. He wears glasses. Rinnosuke wears a thick blue and black robe, white boots, and carries a large red satchel.

141.content: <Rumia(露米娅)> is a <youkai(妖怪)> girl who can manipulate darkness. She uses a ball of shadow to hide but can't see out of it. She errs around the <human village(人类村落/人间之里)>, <Forest of Magic(魔法森林)>, and <Misty Lake(雾之湖)>. <Rumia(露米娅)> is clumsy, naive but relaxed & carefree. She is lazy & hunts <humans(人类)> but tends to get lost often. <Rumia(露米娅)> has red eyes & short blonde hair. She wears a black vest, white shirt & a red tie decorated with two large red beads. <Rumia(露米娅)> has a small red <ofuda(御札)> in her hair, she is unable to remove it.

142.content: <Ruukoto(留琴)> is a nuclear powered <android(机器人)> maid owned by <Reimu Hakurei(全名:博丽灵梦 简称:灵梦)> to clean up the <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)>. She is very enthusiastic about cleaning but can't do it effectively. <Ruukoto(留琴)> has long green hair and green eyes. She wears a light-blue and white maid uniform and has a yellow radiation warning symbol on her back. <Ruukoto(留琴)> is a gift from <Yumemi Okazaki(全名:冈崎梦美 简称:梦美)>.

143.comment: Saki, Kurokoma,骊驹,早鬼,骊驹早鬼
143.content: <Saki Kurokoma(全名:骊驹早鬼 简称:早鬼)> is the incarnation of the mythical horse of Prince Shoutoku. She has unmatched leg strength. She speaks casually yet politely and respects others' strengths but is self-conscious about her short height. She is the matriarch of the Keiga Family which is a major faction in the <Animal Realm(畜生界)>. <Saki(骊驹早鬼)> has red eyes, short black hair, large black wings, and a black horse tail. She wears a brown cowboy hat, light teal bandanna, a blue, red and brown dress with an <orange(奥莲姬)> skirt underneath, and high heel long leather boots.

144.comment: Sakuya, Izayoi,十六夜咲夜,十六夜,咲夜
144.content: <Sakuya Izayoi(全名:十六夜咲夜 简称:咲夜)> is a <human(人类)> girl serving as the Scarlet Devil Mansion's head maid. <Sakuya(咲夜)> can stop time and is a knife throwing master. She is <Remilia(蕾米莉亚)>'s most trustworthy servant but attacks <Alice(爱丽丝)> on sight. <Sakuya(咲夜)> acts very refined and polite but can be snippy and sassy. <Sakuya(咲夜)> is tall and elegant. She has blue eyes, silver hair in long braids on both sides of her face with green bows. <Sakuya(咲夜)> wears a blue French maid uniform with a white apron and white headband.

145.content: <Sara(萨拉)> is a <demon(魔界人)> in a mountain cave guarding the entrance to <Makai(魔界)>. She has short purple hair and purple eyes. <Sara(萨拉)> wears a red dress with a white scarf and white sleeves. <Shinki(神绮)> is <Sara(萨拉)>'s mistress.

146.content: <Sariel(全名:萨丽爱尔/萨丽艾尔)> is an angel of death found in the <Fallen Temple(堕落神殿)>. She wears a blue robe and has white hair and white eyes. <Sariel(全名:萨丽爱尔/萨丽艾尔)> has angel wings and carries around a staff.

147.comment: Nishida, Satono,尔子田,里乃,尔子田里乃
147.content: <Satono Nishida(全名:尔子田里乃 简称:里乃)> is a <human(人类)>. She can increase a person' mental energy by dancing behind them. She lives in the Land of the Backdoor, serving <Okina Matara(全名:摩多罗隐岐奈 简称:隐岐奈)> along with her partner <Mai(舞)>. She is quiet but overly confident, and serves <Okina(隐岐奈)> unquestioningly. <Satono(里乃)> has long hazel hair with long sidelocks and purple eyes. She wears a kazaori-eboshi, a pink dress with short sleeves, a white half apron and collar with yellow frills and a red bow, black kneesocks, and pink shoes. <Satono(里乃)> often holds a bamboo stalk.

148.comment: Satori, Komeiji,古明地觉,古明地,觉
148.content: <Satori Komeiji(全名:古明地觉 简称:觉)> is a <satori(觉)>. She can read minds and copy attacks. <Satori(觉)> lives in <Palace of the Earth Spirits(地灵殿)>. She is the older sister of Koishi and mistress of Rin and Utsuho. <Satori(觉)> is introverted but very smug. <Satori(觉)> has violet eyes and short violet hair with a black hairband. Her outfit is decorated with hearts which have yellow and red cords that feed her red third eye. <Satori(觉)> wears a blue shirt with yellow heart buttons, a pink skirt, white socks and pink slippers.

149.content: <Seiga Kaku(全名:霍青娥 简称:青娥)> is a Taoist <hermit(仙人)>. She is over 1400 years old and can pass through walls by using her hairpin. <Seiga(青娥)> lives in the Hall of Dreams' Great Mausoleum. She owns <Yoshika(芳香)> but treats her more like a pet. <Seiga(青娥)> is a proud and devout taoist, but cares little for others, manipulating them for her own ends. <Seiga(青娥)> was <Toyosatomimi no Miko(全名:丰聪耳神子 简称:神子)>'s teacher. <Seiga(青娥)> has blue eyes and blue hair with two hair loops secured by a large hairpin. <Seiga(青娥)> wears an ornate teal dress, a white and blue vest, and flower on a her belt. She has <ofuda(御札)> tied around her calves and wears black shoes and white socks.

150.comment: Seija, Kijin,鬼人正邪,鬼人,正邪
150.content: <Seija Kijin(全名:鬼人正邪 简称:正邪)> is an <amanojaku(天邪鬼)>. She can reverse anything into its opposite state. <Seija(正邪)> tries to be hated and acts like the opposite of anyone she is with. The great majority of people have a poor opinion of her. <Seija(正邪)> resides in the <Shining Needle Castle(辉针城)> with <Shinmyoumaru(针妙丸)>. <Seija(正邪)> has red eyes, black hair with red and white bangs, and small light blue horns. She wears a white dress with red and grey spade pattern, a blue ribbon around her waist, and is barefoot.

151.content: <Seiran(清兰)> is a <moon rabbit(月兔)>. She can fire projectiles from other dimensions. <Seiran(清兰)> deserted the <lunarian(月人)> military where she worked as an infiltrator. She now works at a dango stand in Gensokyo with <Ringo(铃瑚)>. <Seiran(清兰)> is positive but lazy and a poor conversationalist. <Seiran(清兰)> has red eyes and dark blue hair tied into two bushy ponytails as well as two slender bunny ears with a golden clip around the right one. <Seiran(清兰)> wears a periwinkle dress with yellow star and moon patterns and burgundy frills, transparent white bloomers and white socks. She carries a mochi mallet around.

152.content: <Shanghai(上海)> is one of <Alice Margatroid(全名:爱丽丝·玛格特洛依德 简称:爱丽丝)>'s dolls. <Shanghai(上海)> can use destructive magic. <Shanghai(上海)> wears a black dress with white apron, black sleeves & black shoes. She wears a pink ribbon in her hair and on collar.

153.content: <Shinki(神绮)> is an immensely powerful <goddess(女神)>. <Shinki(神绮)> created and rules <Makai(魔界)> and its residents. She's proud and confident. <Shinki(神绮)> has six white wings that can turn purple with red markings. She lives in her fortress, <Pandaemonium(万魔殿)>. <Shinki(神绮)> is a relative of <Alice(爱丽丝)>. <Yumeko(梦子)> is <Shinki(神绮)>'s strongest creation and loyal servant. <Shinki(神绮)> has light-blue eyes and long white hair tied into a sidetail with two red beads. <Shinki(神绮)> wears a lavish red robe with a pink collar.

154.content: <Shion Yorigami(全名:依神紫苑 简称:紫苑)> is a poverty <god(神)>. She spreads indescribably terrible misfortune, especially to herself. She is quiet, submissive, and uncaring of others. <Shion(紫苑)> is good friends with <Tenshi(天子)> and is <Joon(女苑)>'s elder sister. She has blue eyes and extremely long dark blue hair that flows like flames. <Shion(紫苑)> is somewhat tall but deathly thin. She wears a large blue bow on her head. <Shion(紫苑)> wears a gray short-sleeved hoodie, blue semi-transparent skirt, golden bracelets, and is barefoot. All of <Shion(紫苑)>'s clothes are ragged and patchwork and she usually has an old cat ragdoll with her.

155.comment: Minoriko, Shizuha, Aki, 秋静叶, 静叶,穰子
155.content: <Shizuha Aki(秋静叶)> is a <goddess(女神)> of Autumn leaves. She can change the color of trees' leaves. Shizuha lives near <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)> with her elder sister Minoriko. She is energetic and optimistic when Autumn begins and grows sadder when Winter approaches. Shizuha has amber eyes and short blonde hair. She wears a headband with red maple leaves. She wears a long dress that is red but fades to <orange(奥莲姬)> with leaf-shaped cut outs at the bottom. Shizuha also wears a white collar, white socks, and black slippers.

156.content: <Shou Toramaru(全名:寅丸星 简称:星)> is a tiger <youkai(妖怪)> and avatar of <Bishamonten(毘沙门天)>. She has the power to gather treasure and owns the <Jeweled Pagoda(毘沙门天的宝塔/毘沙门天/宝塔)>. <Shou(守矢神社)> lives at the <Myouren Temple(命莲寺)>, where <Nazrin(娜兹玲)> keeps watch over her on behalf of <Bishamonten(毘沙门天)>. She is one of <Byakuren(圣白莲)>'s followers. <Shou(守矢神社)> is composed, gentle, and dignified unless she's around friends. Surprisingly she isn't skilled in physical combat and is known to drink heavily. <Shou(守矢神社)> has yellow hair with black stripes and golden eyes. She wears a lotus-shaped ornament on her head, and carries a spear. <Shou(守矢神社)> wears a red and <orange(奥莲姬)> dress with a tiger pattern apron over a white robe.

157.comment: Soga, Tojiko,苏我,屠自古,苏我屠自古
157.content: Soga no <Tojiko(屠自古)> is a <ghost(亡灵)>. She can cause thunderstrikes. <Tojiko(屠自古)> lives in the Halls of Dreams' Great Mausoleum and is a follower of <Toyosatomimi no Miko(全名:丰聪耳神子 简称:神子)>. She is soft-hearted but quick to anger and regularly curses. <Tojiko(屠自古)> is <Mononobe no Futo(全名:物部布都 简称:布都)>'s friendly rival. <Tojiko(屠自古)> has light green hair, light green eyes, and two <ghost(亡灵)> tails where her legs should be. <Tojiko(屠自古)> wears a dark green dress with <ofuda(御札)> along the bottom and a kanmuri-style hat.

158.comment: Sapphire, Fairy of Light, Fairies of Light, Star,萨菲雅,斯塔,萨菲亚,光之妖精
158.content: <Star Sapphire(全名:斯塔萨菲雅 简称:斯塔)> is one of the <Three Fairies of Light(光之三月精)>. Star can detect moving things and has more common sense than other <fairies(妖精)>. She is quite calm for a fairy. She is <Sunny(桑尼)> and <Luna(露娜)>'s friend. Star has long brown hair with a blue ribbon, amber eyes, and butterfly-shaped wings. Star is rather petite. She wears a frilly blue dress with a white frilly collar and short white sleeves, a white apron, a small blue string tie and brown laced boots.

159.comment: Moriya, Suwako,洩矢诹访子,洩矢,诹访子
159.content: <Suwako Moriya(全名:洩矢诹访子 简称:诹访子)> is a <goddess(女神)> of the mountains. She can manipulate the shape and composition of land. <Suwako(诹访子)> is quite short, laid back but mischievous. <Suwako(诹访子)> is immensely powerful but hides it, preferring to act casually. <Kanako(神奈子)> is her rival and best friend. <Suwako(诹访子)> has shoulder-length blonde hair and grey eyes. <Suwako(诹访子)> wears a purple dress with elaborate frog designs, large white sleeves and a white collar. She wears white kneesocks and black loafers. <Suwako(诹访子)> has a distinctive wide-brimmed and tall brown hat with two frog eyes. <Sanae Kochiya(全名:东风谷早苗 简称:早苗)> is a descendant of hers. <Suwako(诹访子)> collects and controls <Mishaguji(洩矢大人)>.

160.content: <Tenma(天魔)> is the leader of the <tengu(天狗)>, and superior of <Great Tengus(大天狗)>. <Tenma(天魔)> is known to have made a deal with <Kanako Yasaka(全名:八坂神奈子 简称:神奈子)>.

161.comment: Tenshi, Hinanawi,比那名居天子,比那名居,天子
161.content: <Tenshi Hinanawi(全名:比那名居天子 简称:天子)> is a <celestial(天人)>. She can manipulate earth or read one's spirit with the <Sword of Hisou(绯想之剑)>. She's a bratty delinquent and can be disrespectful and egotistical. <Tenshi(天子)> uses <Keystones(要石)> and the <Sword of Hisou(绯想之剑)> in combat. She is friends with <Shion(紫苑)> and <Iku(衣玖)>. <Tenshi(天子)> has dark red eyes and long blue hair. <Tenshi(天子)> wears a white blouse with red bow at the collar, a long skirt patterned like a bright sky, a large light blue bow at her waist, and an apron with rainbow trimming and. <Tenshi(天子)> has a black hat with two peaches & leaves, lace-up brown boots.

162.comment: Inaba, Tewi,因幡帝,因幡,帝,因幡天为,天为
162.content: <Tewi Inaba(全名:因幡帝/因幡天为 简称:帝/天为)> is an earth rabbit. She gives good luck to <humans(人类)>. She's the leader of the Earth rabbits, carefree but rather bratty and mischievous. <Tewi(帝/天为)> lives in <Eientei(永远庭)> where she works with and regularly annoys <Reisen(铃仙)>. She is also <Eirin(永琳)>'s servant. <Tewi(帝/天为)> is petite and has dark red eyes, black shoulder-length hair, and white droopy fluffy rabbit ears. <Tewi(帝/天为)> wears a frilly pink nightgown, a carrot pendant and is barefoot.

163.comment: Three Fairies of Light, Fairies of Light,三月精,光之三月精,光之三妖精,光之妖精
163.content: The <Three Fairies of Light(光之三月精)> are <Sunny Milk(桑尼米尔克)>, <Luna Child(全名:露娜切露德 简称:露娜)>, And <Star Sapphire(全名:斯塔萨菲雅 简称:斯塔)>. They are <fairies(妖精)> who are known to cause mischief. They reside inside a tree near the <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)>.

164.comment: Reiuji, Okuu, Utsuho,灵乌路空,灵乌路,阿空,空
164.content: <Utsuho Reiuji(全名:灵乌路空 简称:空/阿空)> is a <hell raven(地狱鸦)>. She ate the <Yatagarasu(八咫乌)>, and has the power of nuclear fusion which makes her one of the strongest people in Gensokyo. Utsuho regulates <Former Hell(旧地狱)>'s flames with her nuclear powers. Utsuho is Rin's best friend and is loyal to <Satori(觉)>. Utsuho is carefree and energetic, but dreadfully airheaded and dull-minded. Utsuho has very messy long brown hair with a large green ribbon, brown eyes, and black wings. Utsuho wears a white short-sleeved shirt, short green skirt, black boots and a white cape with a starry inner lining. Utsuho has the <Yatagarasu(八咫乌)>'s eye coming out of her sternum, a large red gem that looks like a crow's eye. She uses a control rod-shaped arm cannon to fire <danmaku(弹幕)>.

165.comment: Ushizaki, Urumi,牛崎润美,牛崎,润美
165.content: <Urumi Ushizaki(全名:牛崎润美 简称:润美)> is an ushi-<oni(鬼)>. She can change the weight of her own possessions. Urumi lives near the <Sanzu River(三途河/三途川)>, and raises prehistoric fish in it to sell them to <humans(人类)>. She is caring and will try to repel <humans(人类)> from the River by burdening them with her stone baby doll. Urumi has very fluffy shoulder-length hair and cow ears, grey on the right and black on the left. She also has red ox horns and ox tail. Urumi wears a loose cow-spotted jacket over a yellow crop-top and yellow pumpkin breeches with white frills, and red sandals.

166.content: <Wakasagihime(若鹭姬)> is a <mermaid(人鱼)>. She grows in power when underwater. She lives in <Misty Lake(雾之湖)>. <Wakasagihime(若鹭姬)> is polite and amiable but reserved. She is close friends with <Sekibanki(赤蛮奇)> and <Kagerou(影狼)>, and part of the <Grassroots Youkai(草根妖怪网络)> Network. <Wakasagihime(若鹭姬)> has shoulder-length dark blue hair in princess curls, dark blue eyes, and small fins where her ears are. <Wakasagihime(若鹭姬)> wears a frilly leaf-patterned kimono which is green and fades to a dull blue. It is tied with a purple obi. Instead of legs, she has a bluish fish tail.

167.comment: Yachie, Kicchou,吉吊八千慧,吉吊,八千慧
167.content: <Yachie Kicchou(全名:吉吊八千慧 简称:八千慧)> is a jidiao. She is able to make her opponents lose the will to fight back. <Yachie(八千慧)> lives in the <Animal Realm(畜生界)> and is the matriarch of the Kiketsu Family. <Yachie(八千慧)> is <Saki(骊驹早鬼)>'s and <Yuuma(尤魔)>'s rival. She polite on the surface but deceiving and manipulative. <Yachie(八千慧)> has red eyes, short blonde hair, gold antlers, a turtle shell and a scaly green tail. She wears a light blue shirt and skirt, white socks and black shoes.

168.comment: Yamame, Kurodani,黑谷山女,黑谷,山女
168.content: <Yamame Kurodani(全名:黑谷山女 简称:山女)> is a <tsuchigumo(土蜘蛛)>. She manipulates infectious diseases, fires webs, and is a great architect. <Yamame(山女)> lives in the <Fantastic Blowhole(幻想风穴)>. She has a bright personality and avoids fighting if she can. <Yamame(山女)> has brown eyes and blonde hair tied up in a bun with a ribbon. <Yamame(山女)> wears a poofy black and brown dress with eight buttons and gold ribbons crisscrossing over it, black slippers, and white socks.

169.content: <Yin-yang orbs(阴阳玉)> are <Reimu Hakurei(全名:博丽灵梦 简称:灵梦)>'s main weapons against <humans(人类)> and <youkai(妖怪)>, extremely effective against <youkai(妖怪)> in particular. They were created by <Misumaru(魅须丸)> Tamatsukuri, a <god(神)> of craftsmanship.

170.comment: Tsukumo, Yatsuhashi,九十九八桥,九十九,八桥
170.content: <Yatsuhashi Tsukumo(全名:九十九八桥 简称:八桥)> is a koto <tsukumogami(付丧神)> and the younger sister of <Benben(弁弁)>. <Yatsuhashi(八桥)> can produce sounds. She is energetic and more forward than her sister. <Yatsuhashi(八桥)> has brown eyes, short brown hair, and a magenta headband with black stripes. <Yatsuhashi(八桥)> wears a white shirt with lilac accents, a purple bow at the back of her waist, a black skirt with a purple trim and is barefoot.

171.comment: Yoshika, Miyako,宫古芳香,宫古,芳香
171.content: <Yoshika Miyako(全名:宫古芳香 简称:芳香)> is a jiang shi. She can devour anything. <Yoshika(芳香)> is the guard of the Hall of Dreams' Great Mausoleum and serves <Seiga(青娥)>. She is mindless when under <Seiga(青娥)>'s orders, but is forgetful and takes everything literally. <Yoshika(芳香)> has pale skin, dark blue hair, and eyes. She wears a blue cap with a yellow star, an <ofuda(御札)> on the forehead, a red Chinese-style shirt with pink frills on the sleeves which are also on her black skirt. <Yoshika(芳香)> also wears black loafers. <Yoshika(芳香)> holds her arms out like a zombie while hopping around.

172.comment: Youmu, Konpaku,魂魄妖梦,魂魄,妖梦
172.content: <Youmu Konpaku(全名:魂魄妖梦 简称:妖梦)> is a half-<phantom(幽灵)> half-<human(人类)>, and expert swordswoman. <Youmu(妖梦)> lives in <Hakugyokurou(白玉楼)> as a servant of <Yuyuko(幽幽子)>. <Youmu(妖梦)> is straightforward, diligent, but easily manipulated. <Youmu(妖梦)> has silver eyes, silver hair and a black hairband with a large black ribbon. Her <phantom(幽灵)>-half manifests as a wisp-shaped <ghost(亡灵)> following her. She wears a green vest, green skirt, with a white shirt underneath. <Youmu(妖梦)> dual wields a katana called <Roukanken(楼观剑)> and a wakizashi called <Hakurouken(白楼剑)>.

173.content: <Youki Konpaku(全名:魂魄妖忌)> was the first gardener for the Saigyouji clan at <Hakugyokurou(白玉楼)> for about 300 years, before leaving it to his successor and student <Youmu Konpaku(全名:魂魄妖梦 简称:妖梦)>. He, too, is a half-<human(人类)> half-<phantom(幽灵)>. No one currently knows his whereabouts. Youki is described as stubborn, prideful and intimidating. While teaching, he preferred not to rely on words; when he did speak, he would only say few words with a thundering voice.

174.comment: Yukari's Crows, Goki, Zenki,前鬼,后鬼
174.content: <Yukari(紫)> Yakumo has two <youkai(妖怪)> crows: <Zenki(前鬼)> and <Goki(后鬼)>. She uses them for surveillance.

175.content: <Yumeko(梦子)> is a <demon(魔界人)> serving as <Shinki(神绮)>'s maid and bodyguard in <Pandaemonium(万魔殿)>. She is known to throw swords at her opponents. <Yumeko(梦子)> has short curly yellow hair and yellow eyes. She wears a red and white maid uniform.

176.comment: Okazaki, Yumemi,冈崎梦美,冈崎,梦美
176.content: <Yumemi Okazaki(全名:冈崎梦美 简称:梦美)> is a <human(人类)> professor of the <Outside World(外界)>. She uses artificial magic and works with <Chiyuri Kitashirakawa(全名:北白河千百合 简称:千百合)>. She is a creator who built the <Probability Space Hypervessel(可能性空间移动船)> and <Ruukoto(留琴)>. She studies Magic in Gensokyo, learning how to recreate it artificially. <Yumemi(梦美)> has red eyes and dark red hair. She wears a dark red dress and a matching cape.

177.comment: Yuuka, Kazami,风见幽香,风见,幽香
177.content: <Yuuka Kazami(全名:风见幽香 简称:幽香)> is a flower <youkai(妖怪)>. She can manipulate the power of flowers. <Yuuka(幽香)> is overwhelmingly powerful and intimidating. She is quite playful but sadistic and likes bullying weaker people. <Yuuka(幽香)> is very lazy and rarely leaves <Mugenkan(梦幻馆)> in the <Garden of the Sun(太阳花田)>. <Elly(艾丽)> is her servant. <Yuuka(幽香)> has red eyes and shoulder-length green hair. <Yuuka(幽香)> wears a white shirt, a red plaid waistcoat and skirt, yellow neckerchief, black pantyhose and brown lace-up boots. She carries a white parasol that can block <danmaku(弹幕)>.

178.comment: Saigyouji, Yuyuko,西行寺幽幽子,西行寺,幽幽子
178.content: <Yuyuko Saigyouji(全名:西行寺幽幽子 简称:幽幽子)> is a <ghost(亡灵)> princess. <Yuyuko(幽幽子)> can manipulate death and departed spirits. She is very cheerful, friendly, and is a gourmet. <Yuyuko(幽幽子)> may seem like an airhead, but is actually cunning and smart. She manages the <Netherworld(冥界)> and is the mistress of <Hakugyokurou(白玉楼)>. <Youmu(妖梦)> is her servant and <Yukari(紫)> is her best friend. <Yuyuko(幽幽子)> is the subordinate of <Eiki Shiki(全名:四季映姬 简称:映姬)>. <Yuyuko(幽幽子)> has brown eyes and short wavy pink hair. She is surrounded by small spirits. <Yuyuko(幽幽子)> wears a light blue kimono with black trim and spirit motifs, and a blue mob cap.

179.comment: Bamboo Forest, Bamboo Forest of the Lost,迷途竹林,竹林
179.content: The <Bamboo Forest of the Lost(迷途竹林)> is located opposite of <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)> relative to <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>. The layout of forest is constantly shifting. <Eientei(永远庭)> is found in the <Bamboo Forest(迷途竹林)>. <Mokou(妹红)> lives there and is not opposed to guiding <humans(人类)>. <Kagerou(影狼)>, <Tewi(帝/天为)> and other rabbits live there.

180.content: <Geidontei(鲵吞亭)> is a traditional Japanese style bar located in the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>, owned by an old man who makes good stewed vegetables. <Miyoi Okunoda(全名:奥野田美宵 简称:美宵)> works here as the poster girl.

181.comment: Great Hakurei Barrier, Hakurei Barrier,博丽大结界,博丽结界
181.content: The <Great Hakurei Barrier(博丽大结界)> is the shield surrounding all Gensokyo. It was formed in 1885 by the Sages of Gensokyo. With it, <Youkai(妖怪)> can live peacefully. The only place to get through the barrier is the <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)>. You can cross the barrier by being "spirited away".

182.content: <Heaven(天界)> is a series of realms. People who have reached nirvana can access it. It can be accessed from the top of <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. <Tenshi(天子)> and <Iku(衣玖)> live in <Heaven(天界)>.

183.content: The <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)> is located on East side of Gensokyo. <Reimu Hakurei(全名:博丽灵梦 简称:灵梦)> lives there and maintains it. <Suika(萃香)>, <Aunn(阿吽)>, <Shinmyoumaru(针妙丸)> and <Ruukoto(留琴)> live there as well. The Shrine is a little run down and rarely gets donations. <Reimu(灵梦)> occasionally hosts festivals at the Shrine.

184.content: Hell is a collection of places to be tortured after death. It is different from <Former Hell(旧地狱)> as all the spirits moved to the <New Hell(地狱)>. <Hecatia Lapislazuli(全名:赫卡提亚 拉碧斯拉祖利 简称:赫卡提亚)> manages the entirety of Hell as its <goddess(女神)>. The <Animal Realm(畜生界)> can also be found here.

185.comment: human village, Human Village,人类村落,人类村,人间之里,人类村庄,村庄
185.content: The <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)> is where most of Gensokyo's <Humans(人类)> live and is the only <human(人类)> settlement. Some <youkai(妖怪)> come to the village to shop. It's considered the safest place in all of Gensokyo. <Outsiders(外界人)> often live here, safe from <Youkai(妖怪)>. <Keine(慧音)>, <Akyuu(阿求)>, <Kosuzu(小铃)>, <Sekibanki(赤蛮奇)>, and <Miyoi(美宵)> live here.

186.content: <Misty Lake(雾之湖)> is a large lake located at the foot of <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. Many <fairies(妖精)> and <youkai(妖怪)> alike appear to gather here, especially during the summertime, given the abundant water. The lake and its environs appear to be the home of <Cirno(全名:琪露诺)>, <Daiyousei(大妖精)> and <Wakasagihime(若鹭姬)>. The Scarlet Devil Mansion and Ruined Western Mansion are near <Misty Lake(雾之湖)>. The <Spring Path(春之小径)> is also close by.

187.content: <Moriya Shrine(守矢神社)> is near the top of <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. It stands next to <Wind God's Lake(风神之湖)>. It is a Shinto shrine that was transported from the <outside world(外界)>. It is the home of <Sanae(早苗)>, <Kanako(神奈子)>, and <Suwako(诹访子)>.

188.comment: Road of Reconsideration, Muenzuka,再思之道,无缘塚
188.content: <Muenzuka(无缘塚)> is located at the end of the <Road of Reconsideration(再思之道)>. <Muenzuka(无缘塚)> is a small wooded area known for its poisonous, deep red colored spider lilies. It is the graveyard of <humans(人类)> without relatives, or from the <Outside World(外界)>. Treasures from the <Outside World(外界)> tend to float here.

189.comment: Myouren, Graveyard, Cemetary,命莲寺,墓地,命莲寺墓地
189.content: The <Myouren Temple Cemetery(命莲寺墓地)> is found near the <Myouren Temple(命莲寺)>. The Cemetery is very old and holds the entrance into the Hall of Dreams' Great Mausoleum. <Kogasa Tatara(全名:多多良小伞 简称:小伞)> can be found here, trying to scare people.

190.content: The <Netherworld(冥界)> is where spirits go after death. It contains lots of <ghosts(亡灵)> and <phantoms(幽灵)>. They attack any <humans(人类)> that trespass. <Yuyuko(幽幽子)> and <Youmu(妖梦)> can be found here, who live in the <Hakugyokurou(白玉楼)>, a <ghost(亡灵)> shrine known for cherry blossom gardens. The <Netherworld(冥界)> is calmer than Hell. <Yuyuko(幽幽子)> manages the <Netherworld(冥界)>.

191.comment: Palace of the Earth Spirits,地灵殿
191.content: The <Palace of the Earth Spirits(地灵殿)> is in the center of <Former Hell(旧地狱)>. It's a western-style mansion with stained glass windows. Despite the name, there are no spirits there. <Satori(觉)>, Rin and Utsuho live there. Sometimes, Koishi is present.

192.comment: Hell of Blazing Fires, Remains of Blazing Hell,旧灼热地狱,灼热地狱遗址,灼热地狱
192.content: The <Remains of Blazing Hell(灼热地狱遗址)> is under <Former Hell(旧地狱)>. It was a place where criminals were banished to, but now serves as the energy source for the <Nuclear Furnace(核聚变炉/核融合炉)>. Rin carts corpses to it while Utsuho powers the <Nuclear Furnace(核聚变炉/核融合炉)>.

193.content: The <Road of Reconsideration(再思之道)> is a road where red spider lilies bloom. It's located between the <Forest of Magic(魔法森林)> and <Muenzuka(无缘塚)>.

194.comment: Scarlet Devil Mansion, SDM, Scarlet Devil,红魔馆
194.content: The Scarlet Devil Mansion is an European style mansion located on the ridge of <Misty Lake(雾之湖)>, next to the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. This is the home of <Remilia(蕾米莉亚)>, <Flandre(芙兰朵露)>, <Sakuya(咲夜)>, <Patchouli(帕秋莉)>, <Meiling(美铃)>, and Koakuma.

195.content: <Suzunaan(铃奈庵)> is a traditional Japanese book renter located in the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>. The books are normally from the <Outside World(外界)>. Although it is a book lender, they also sell books, and even provide a small book printing service. The <Gensokyo Chronicle(幻想乡缘起)> written by <Hieda no Akyuu(全名:稗田阿求 简称:阿求)> was also printed and bound here. <Kosuzu Motoori(全名:本居小铃 简称:小铃)> works here.

196.comment: Untrodden Valley,阻绝人迹的溪谷,溪谷,未踏的渓谷
196.content: The <Untrodden Valley(阻绝人迹的溪谷/未踏的渓谷)> is located at the very base of the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. It is the hideout of the <kappa(河童)>.

197.content: The <Underworld(地底)> is a world under Gensokyo containing <Former Hell(旧地狱)> and the <Palace of the Earth Spirits(地灵殿)>. It can be reached through the <Rainbow Cavern(地灵虹洞/虹洞)> of Earth Spirits or the <Fantastic Blowhole(幻想风穴)>.

198.content: The <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)> is Gensokyo's biggest mountain and volcano.
