It has many known locations such as the <Wind God's Lake(风神之湖)>, <Moriya Shrine(守矢神社)>, the <Untrodden Valley(阻绝人迹的溪谷/未踏的渓谷)>, and the <Great Youkai Forest(妖怪的树海)> at the base. It is ruled by the <Tengu(天狗)>. A number of <gods(神)> can also be found on the mountain, <Kanako(神奈子)> having the highest rank among them.

199.content: The <Youkai Trail(兽道)> is located near the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>. <Mystia(米斯蒂娅)> operates a food stand there to scam <humans(人类)>.

200.content: <Spell card rules(符卡规则)> are laws forbidding Gensokyo residents to kill others. They are enforced throughout all of Gensokyo. Breaking them results in extermination. These rules rejects a system where the strongest has the right to rule, and gives <humans(人类)> and weaker <youkai(妖怪)> a chance to have a word in conflicts.

201.content: <Danmaku(弹幕)> is a barrage of bullets made from magic. To win a <danmaku(弹幕)> battle, one must dodge or outperform the pattern of projectiles.

202.content: <Youkai(妖怪)> are spiritual beings that survive on belief. They often take on <human(人类)> forms, usually of cute girls. They cannot be defeated by attacks that do not have enough "meaning." <Youkai(妖怪)> mainly feed on <humans(人类)> or <human(人类)> fear.

203.content: <Spell cards(符卡)> are powerful magical patterns that enhances the user's attack and defensive abilities for a short time. They are often flashy. Users have to call them out before using them.

204.comment: Raiko, Horikawa,堀川雷鼓,堀川,雷鼓
204.content: <Raiko Horikawa(全名:堀川雷鼓 简称:雷鼓)> is a taiko drum <tsukumogami(付丧神)>. She can make anything follow a rhythm. She is laid-back and friendly, putting her freedom and that of other <tsukumogami(付丧神)> above everything else. Raiko has short wavy red hair and red eyes. She wears a black and red flannel shirt tucked in a short white skirt, has a purple tie, a white blazer, short purple boots with red laces and bass drum mallets attached to the heels. She sits on a flying ornate drum kit with a flower pattern.

205.comment: Wolf Tengu, White Wolf Tengu, Tengu,白狼天狗,狼天狗,天狗
205.content: <White wolf tengu(白狼天狗)> are anthropomorphic white wolves with a <human(人类)> body structure. They are the protectors of the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)> and will attack trespassers. <White wolf tengu(白狼天狗)> are known to be avid players of shogi.

206.content: <Shinigami(死神)> are grim reapers. They are tasked to guide spirits to be judged and ferry them across the <Sanzu River(三途河/三途川)>. <Shinigami(死神)> wield scythes and some can see the life spans of mortals.

207.content: <Tsukumogami(付丧神)> are objects or tools inhabited by a vengeful spirit seeking revenge on the <humans(人类)> that discarded them. <Tsukumogami(付丧神)> appear as <humans(人类)> carrying the objects they once were.

208.content: <Moon rabbits(月兔)> are from the moon and are stronger than earth rabbits. They can transform into <humans(人类)> with rabbit ears and use telepathy. <Moon Rabbits(月兔)> are seen as tools by <Lunarians(月人)> and are used for farming, making medicine, cleaning and as soldiers. A few fled to Gensokyo.

209.content: <Kitsune(狐/妖狐)> are <youkai(妖怪)> foxes with up to nine tails. They have incredible magical powers and can shapeshift.

210.content: <Nekomata(猫又)> are <youkai(妖怪)> cats with multiple tails. They use necromancy or shamanism and grow more powerful every ten years when they grow a new tail.

211.content: <Fairies(妖精)> in Gensokyo are playful, mischievous childlike beings. They are born from nature and indestructible, reappearing unless their habitat is destroyed. <Fairies(妖精)> are made of pure life force. They come in all shapes and colors based on their element.

key: 芙兰朵露 斯卡蕾特
212.comment: Flandre, Scarlet Devil,芙兰朵露,斯卡蕾特,芙兰朵露 斯卡蕾特,绯红恶魔
212.content: <Flandre Scarlet(全名:芙兰朵露 斯卡蕾特 简称:芙兰/芙兰朵露)> is a <vampire(吸血鬼)> living in the Scarlet Devil Mansion. She has the power to destroy anything, but does not control that ability well. <Flandre(芙兰朵露)> is <Remilia(蕾米莉亚)>'s little sister. She scares Scarlet Devil Mansion residents due to her unstable behavior, as she was jailed for 495 years by <Remilia(蕾米莉亚)>. Even then, she tries to play with guests, her sister and her servants, sometimes too insistently. <Flandre(芙兰朵露)> is childlike, innocent and excitable but sassy. <Flandre(芙兰朵露)> has red eyes, short blonde hair, and a short left sidetail. She wears a red dress and vest, a pink mob cap with red ribbon, and has a pair of rainbow crystal wings.

213.comment: Ichirin, Kumoi, Unzan,云居一轮,云居,一轮,云山
213.content: <Ichirin Kumoi(全名:云居一轮 简称:云居/一轮)> is a <youkai(妖怪)> and <Nyuudou(入道)> user. She has the ability to control <Unzan(云山)> as well as her own <danmaku(弹幕)> powers. <Ichirin(一轮)> is rather mature and tenacious but too eager to see good in people. She guards the <Myouren Temple(命莲寺)> and is one of <Byakuren(圣白莲)>'s followers. <Ichirin(一轮)> has wavy shoulder-length blue hair and blue eyes. She wears a white and blue dress with a blue veil, a red orb around her neck, and a black and gold Japanese-style kesa she wears over her shoulder. <Ichirin(一轮)> also wears white shoes and carries a large golden ring to control <Unzan(云山)>.

214.comment: Keine, Kamishirasawa,上白泽慧音,上白泽,慧音
214.content: <Keine Kamishirasawa(全名:上白泽慧音 简称:慧音)> is a <were-hakutaku(白泽/半白泽)>. She has the power to create history as a <human(人类)> and eat history as a <hakutaku(白泽/半白泽)>. <Keine(慧音)> is a teacher and guardian of the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>. She is friendly with <humans(人类)> but not <youkai(妖怪)> and hides her <youkai(妖怪)> identity. <Keine(慧音)> is friends with <Mokou(妹红)>. <Keine(慧音)> is tall and has silvery blue hair and brown eyes as a <human(人类)>; but silvery green hair and red eyes when in her <hakutaku(白泽/半白泽)> form. <Keine(慧音)> wears a blue dress over a white frilly skirt, and a blue hat with a very large red ribbon. In her <Hakutaku(白泽/半白泽)> form, she has horns with a red bow on the left one, and her dress is green.

215.comment: Onozuka, Komachi,小野塚小町,小野塚,小町
215.content: <Komachi Onozuka(全名:小野塚小町 简称:小町)> is a <shinigami(死神)>. She can manipulate distances. <Komachi(小町)> ferries spirits across the <Sanzu River(三途河/三途川)> and is <Eiki(映姬)>'s subordinate. Her boat is called the "Titanic." She is lazy, carefree, and chatty. <Komachi(小町)> dislikes when people disrespect <Eiki(映姬)>. <Komachi(小町)> is imposingly tall, has red eyes and shoulder-length red hair in two ponytails tied with hair beads. <Komachi(小町)> carries a scythe. She wears a white dress underneath a blue vest, has an obi with a large coin tied to it, and wears platform sandals.

216.comment: Mononobe, Futo,物部布都,物部,布都
216.content: <Mononobe no Futo(全名:物部布都 简称:布都)> is a Taoist practicing <hermit(仙人)>. She can manipulate feng shui and carries a lot of plates to use as weapons. She lives in the Hall of Dreams' Great Mausoleum. <Futo(布都)> is over 1400 years old. She is gentle at heart, but is stuck in the past and talks in an antiquated manner. <Futo(布都)> is a follower of <Toyosatomimi no Miko(全名:丰聪耳神子 简称:神子)> and friendly rivals with Soga no <Tojiko(屠自古)>. <Futo(布都)> has grey eyes and hair. She wears a pink Heian Era karinginu with a purple skirt. She also wears a distinct eboshi on her head.

217.comment: Okina, Matara,摩多罗隐岐奈,摩多罗,隐岐奈
217.content: <Okina Matara(全名:摩多罗隐岐奈 简称:隐岐奈)> is a secret <god(神)>. She can create doors on the back of anything to manipulate its energy. <Okina(隐岐奈)> lives in the <Land of the Back Door(后户之国)>. She's prideful, and a huge showoff, favoring those who think highly of her. <Okina(隐岐奈)> is one of the Sages of Gensokyo. <Satono(里乃)> and <Mai(舞)> are her servants. <Okina(隐岐奈)> has long, blonde hair and gold eyes. She wears a yellow tabard adorned with a pattern of green stars.

218.comment: Patchouli Knowledge, Patche, Patchouli, Patchy,帕秋莉,诺蕾姬,帕秋莉 诺蕾姬,帕琪
218.content: <Patchouli Knowledge(全名:帕秋莉诺蕾姬 简称:帕秋莉)> is a <youkai(妖怪)> <magician(魔法使)>. She is very skilled at all types of magic. <Patchouli(帕秋莉)> is the librarian of the Scarlet Devil Mansion. <Patchouli(帕秋莉)> is a stereotypical shut-in and is not very sociable, but quite witty. She is friends with <Marisa(魔理沙)>, who steals her books regularly, and as a fellow <magician(魔法使)>, is acquainted with <Alice(爱丽丝)>. Koakuma is <Patchouli(帕秋莉)>'s servant. She is physically weak and asthmatic. <Patchouli(帕秋莉)> has long purple hair and purple eyes, wearing a pink nightgown and night cap with a gold crescent moon pin.

219.content: <Ran Yakumo(全名:八云蓝 简称:蓝)> is a <kitsune(狐/妖狐)> and <shikigami(式神)> of <Yukari(紫)>. She has a <shikigami(式神)> of her own, <Chen(全名:橙)>, and is very powerful by herself. Ran performs domestic duties for <Yukari(紫)>, and does maintenance on the <Great Hakurei Barrier(博丽大结界)>. She is peaceful and gentle. Ran has yellow eyes, short blonde hair, and nine fox tails. Ran is fairly tall. She wears a white dress with purple cuffs and collar, and an indigo tabard with white print. Ran has a light pink two-tipped hat decorated with amulets hiding her fox ears.

220.comment: Hakurei, Reimu,博丽灵梦,博丽,灵梦
220.content: <Reimu Hakurei(全名:博丽灵梦 简称:灵梦)> is a <human(人类)> shrine maiden. <Reimu(灵梦)>'s duty is to exterminate <youkai(妖怪)>. She maintains the <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)>. <Reimu(灵梦)> is aloof to strangers, ruthless to enemies; but a great friend. She’s prideful and quite arrogant due to it. She is quick to anger, but she’s also quick to forget. She is responsible for the safety of Gensokyo and maintains balance between <humans(人类)> & <youkai(妖怪)>. <Reimu(灵梦)> is <Marisa(魔理沙)>'s best friend, rivals with <Sanae(早苗)>, and <Yukari(紫)> is her mentor of sorts.

221.comment: Orin, Kaenbyou, Rin,火焰猫燐,火焰猫,燐,阿燐
221.content: Rin Kaenbyou or "<Orin(阿燐)>" is a <kasha(火车)>. She can talk to spirits and control vengeful ones. Rin carries corpses to <Former Hell(旧地狱)>'s flames using a hand cart. She is positive and energetic. Rin is one of <Satori(觉)>'s pets and Utsuho is her best friend. She has black cat ears, red eyes, and fiery red hair tied into twin braids with black ribbons. Rin wears a very dark green dress with green frills, several anklets and a ribbon around her left leg, and black ribbon pumps.

222.comment: Sukuna, Shinmyoumaru,少名针妙丸,少名,针妙丸
222.content: <Shinmyoumaru Sukuna(全名:少名针妙丸 简称:针妙丸)> is a young <inchling(小人)> princess. She can use the <Miracle Mallet(万宝槌)> and the Shining Needle Sword. <Shinmyoumaru(针妙丸)> lives in the <Shining Needle Castle(辉针城)> with <Seija(正邪)>. <Shinmyoumaru(针妙丸)> acts and speaks like a child and is incredibly gullible. She has short lavender hair and purple eyes and is only a few inches tall. <Shinmyoumaru(针妙丸)> wears a pink kimono with a floral pattern, a black obi and travels around in a floating bowl. She is barefoot.

223.content: <Sekibanki(赤蛮奇)> is a <rokurokubi(辘轳首)>. She can make her head fly or stretch her neck out. <Sekibanki(赤蛮奇)> lives in the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)> under the guise of a <human(人类)>. She is a little prideful but avoids people and is rather cynical. She is good friends with <Kagerou(影狼)> and <Wakasagihime(若鹭姬)> and is a part of the <Grassroots Youkai(草根妖怪网络)> Network. <Sekibanki(赤蛮奇)> has short red hair and red eyes. <Sekibanki(赤蛮奇)> wears a red and blue capelet she hides her lower face with, a black and red long sleeved shirt, and a red skirt.

224.comment: Sunny, Sunny Milk,桑尼米尔克,桑尼,米尔克
224.content: <Sunny Milk(桑尼米尔克)> is one of the <Three Fairies of Light(光之三月精)>. She has the power to refract light to make things invisible. <Sunny(桑尼)> is very curious about everything, and very energetic. She is <Luna(露娜)>'s and Star's friend. <Sunny(桑尼)> has short red hair held in tufty twintails with red ribbons, blue eyes, and a pair of oblong wings. <Sunny(桑尼)> is rather petite. She wears a red and white dress with many frills, long sleeves, a red obi and a yellow neckerchief, brown shoes, and a white maid headband.

225.comment: Suika, Ibuki,伊吹萃香,伊吹,萃香
225.content: <Suika Ibuki(全名:伊吹萃香 简称:萃香)> is an <oni(鬼)>. She can manipulate density and sparseness. She is jolly and childish but immensely strong. <Suika(萃香)> enjoys festivals and parties and is always, without exception, drunk. She often stays at the <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)> and is friends with <Reimu(灵梦)>, <Yukari(紫)>, <Yuugi(勇仪)> and <Miyoi(美宵)>. <Suika(萃香)> has two long horns on her head with a red ribbon on the left, long brown hair with a large red ribbon in it, and brown eyes. She wears a tattered pale pink blouse, a long purple and pink skirt with flame patterns, cloth bracers and ribbon pumps. <Suika(萃香)> carries a large sake gourd. <Suika(萃香)> is quite short and petite.

226.comment: Usami, Sumireko,宇佐见堇子,宇佐见,堇子
226.content: <Sumireko Usami(全名:宇佐见堇子 简称:堇子)> is an <outsider(外界人)> <human(人类)>. She can use psychic powers and access Gensokyo through her dreams. She has a superiority complex. <Sumireko(堇子)> considers <Reimu(灵梦)> and <Marisa(魔理沙)> her friends and <Mokou(妹红)> her friendly rival. <Sumireko(堇子)> has brown eyes and messy shoulder-length brown hair. She wears a black hat with a white bow along with under-framed red glasses, a purple plaid skirt and matching sleeveless dress over a white blouse with long sleeves. <Sumireko(堇子)> wears a black bolo tie, white gloves, white socks with ribbons, black shoes, black cloak with red, rune-inscribed inner lining, and carries a smartphone that she takes lots of pictures with.

227.comment: Toyosatomimi, Miko,丰聪耳神子,丰聪耳,神子
227.content: <Toyosatomimi no Miko(全名:丰聪耳神子 简称:神子)> is a saint and <hermit(仙人)>. She is the reincarnation of Prince Shoutoku, who spread Buddhism but is now a follower of Taoism. Miko is immortal, can listen to ten conversations at the same time and use Taoist magic. Miko is known to be casual and often jokes around. She lives in the Hall of Dreams' Great Mausoleum or <Senkai(仙界)>. <Mononobe no Futo(全名:物部布都 简称:布都)> and Soga no <Tojiko(屠自古)> are her followers. <Seiga(青娥)> is Miko's taoism mentor. Miko has platinum blonde hair styled like tufty horns and pale brown eyes. She wears purple earmuffs, a white dress over a purple skirt, and a large purple cape. Miko carries her Seven Star Sword.

228.comment: Wriggle, Nightbug,莉格露,奈特巴格,莉格露 奈特巴格
228.content: <Wriggle Nightbug(全名:莉格露 奈特巴格)> is a firefly <youkai(妖怪)>. She can control other insects. Wriggle is energetic, caring about nature, but very forgetful and easily angered, especially by people who insult insects. Wriggle has blue eyes, teal hair, and bug-like antennae. She wears a white shirt, a black cape with red lining that looks like insect wings, blue shorts, and red shoes.

229.content: <Yuki(雪)> is a witch who specializes in fire magic. She lives in <Makai(魔界)> in the <World of Ice and Snow(冰雪世界)> along with <Mai(舞)>. <Yuki(雪)> has yellow hair and yellow eyes. She wears a dark red hat with a pink ribbon and a dark red and pink dress.

230.content: <Yukari(紫)> Yakumo is a unique <youkai(妖怪)>. She can manipulate the boundaries of anything. <Yukari(紫)> likes to sleep, and enjoys life freely. She is one of the Sages of Gensokyo. <Yukari(紫)> is a manipulative mastermind and is secretive about her real goals. <Yukari(紫)> is friendly towards <Reimu(灵梦)> but messes with her. <Yukari(紫)> is best friends with <Yuyuko(幽幽子)>, friends with <Suika(萃香)>, and Ran is her <Shikigami(式神)>. <Yukari(紫)> is tall and mature-looking. <Yukari(紫)> has gold eyes and very long blonde hair with many red ribbons. She wears a purple tabard with trigrams over a pale pink Western dress with black sleeve cuffs. <Yukari(紫)> wears a pink mob cap with a red ribbon, and usually carries a parasol.

231.comment: Yuugi, Hoshiguma,星熊勇仪,星熊,勇仪
231.content: <Yuugi Hoshiguma(全名:星熊勇仪 简称:勇仪)> is an <oni(鬼)>. She wields the power of unexplained phenomena. <Yuugi(勇仪)> lives in <Former Hell(旧地狱)>'s <Hot Spring Town(旧地狱温泉街)>, which she manages. She is very blunt, straightforward, and dislikes weakness. <Yuugi(勇仪)>'s physical strength defies description. <Yuugi(勇仪)> is <Suika(萃香)>'s best friend. <Yuugi(勇仪)> has red eyes, a single long starry red horn on her forehead, and long blonde hair. She wears a white short-sleeved shirt with red trim, a dark blue semi-transparent skirt with red highlights, and geta sandals. <Yuugi(勇仪)> has broken manacles on her wrists and carries a starry red sake dish that improves any sake poured in it.

232.content: <Kasha(火车)> are hell cats who steal corpses from funerals and bring them to the Hell of Blazing Flames as fuel to regulate its heat.

233.content: <Makai(魔界)> is a location behind the <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)> in the mountains. Access to it is sealed, but there are ways to go around it. It is created by <Shinki(神绮)>. A toxic miasma fills the air, which is poisonous to normal beings but increases magical power. It houses mostly <demons(魔界人)>. The <Ruins of Vina(维纳的废墟)>, <Fallen Temple(堕落神殿)>, <Makai(魔界)> City, <World of Ice and Snow(冰雪世界)>, <Pandaemonium(万魔殿)>, <Wonderland(仙境)>, and Hokkai are found in <Makai(魔界)>.

234.content: The <Fallen Temple(堕落神殿)> is located somewhere in <Makai(魔界)>. It's a giant broken down temple with a giant crucifix hanging in the lobby. It houses the angel of death <Sariel(全名:萨丽爱尔/萨丽艾尔)>.

235.comment: Makai, Yuki, Mai, World of Ice and Snow,魔界,雪,舞,冰雪世界
235.content: The <World of Ice and Snow(冰雪世界)> is located somewhere in <Makai(魔界)>. It's a barren snowy wasteland with a frozen river running through. <Yuki(雪)> and <Mai(舞)> live around here.

236.content: The <Wonderland(仙境)> is a location in <Makai(魔界)> created in the distant past by <Alice Margatroid(全名:爱丽丝·玛格特洛依德 简称:爱丽丝)>. <Alice(爱丽丝)> visits it sometimes.

237.content: <Pandaemonium(万魔殿)> is located in <Makai(魔界)> right after the <World of Ice and Snow(冰雪世界)>. It's a giant Fortress made of a crystalline material built by and houses <Shinki(神绮)>. It's in a devastated state after <Shinki(神绮)> lost control.

238.content: <Ellen(全名:爱莲/艾伦/艾莲)> is a witch wandering Gensokyo. She looks very young but she's actually immortal while having a childish mindset. <Ellen(全名:爱莲/艾伦/艾莲)> is short, has long blonde hair, and yellow eyes. She wears a red and white dress and a red bow on her head.

239.content: <Elly(艾丽)> is a former <shinigami(死神)>. She is the servant of <Yuuka Kazami(全名:风见幽香 简称:幽香)> and gatekeeper of <Mugenkan(梦幻馆)>. She's excitable but lonely. <Elly(艾丽)> uses a scythe to fight. She has curly shoulder-length blonde hair and yellow eyes. <Elly(艾丽)> wears a pink hat with a red ribbon, a dark red and pink dress and red shoes.

240.content: <Louise(全名:露易兹/路易斯)> is a <demon(魔界人)> found in <Makai(魔界)>. She's really polite and will often try not to push things too far. She wants to leave <Makai(魔界)>. <Louise(全名:露易兹/路易斯)> has yellow eyes and short yellow hair. She wears a white hat with a purple birron and a white dress with a purple collar.

241.content: <Mini-Hakkero(迷你八卦炉)> is a magical device owned by <Marisa Kirisame(全名:雾雨魔理沙 简称:魔理沙)>. It can fire the <Master Spark(极限火花)>. The <Mini-Hakkero(迷你八卦炉)> is a hand-sized, octagonal piece of wood inscribed with eight Taoist trigrams. Its internal components are made from hihiirokane. It can generate intense heat and magical energy, and the continuous beam it fires looks like a giant laser of rainbow energy.

242.content: <Kourindou(香霖堂)> is an antique store owned by Rinnosuke located between the <Forest of Magic(魔法森林)> and the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>. It supposedly sells antiques and has an extensive inventory. It is mostly a place to barter for items from the <outside world(外界)>. <Kourindou(香霖堂)> gets very little customers and is rather poorly maintained. <Marisa(魔理沙)> visits <Kourindou(香霖堂)> regularly.

243.content: <Master Spark(极限火花)> is <Marisa(魔理沙)>'s signature spellcard. The <Master Spark(极限火花)> is a gigantic laser beam fired from the <Mini-Hakkero(迷你八卦炉)>. It is incredibly strong and intimidating. The idea was stolen from <Yuuka Kazami(全名:风见幽香 简称:幽香)>.

244.content: The <Purification Rod(驱魔棒)> or "<gohei(御币)>" is owned by <Reimu Hakurei(全名:博丽灵梦 简称:灵梦)>. It is used to exterminate <youkai(妖怪)>. <Reimu(灵梦)> uses her <gohei(御币)> to fire <danmaku(弹幕)>.

245.comment: Kakashi Spirit News, Hatate,花果子念报,果,羽立,极
245.content: <Kakashi Spirit News(花果子念报)> is ran by <Hatate Himekaidou(全名:姬海棠果/姬海棠羽立/姬海棠极 简称:果/羽立/极)> and is the rival of <Bunbunmaru Newspaper(文文。新闻)>. It uses spirit photography, so the articles are very in-depth and informative, but also from the past, so the information is outdated.

246.content: <Keystones(要石)> are holy rocks that can suppress earthquakes or cause them. <Tenshi(天子)> rides them and uses them to fight. They are lumps of black granite wrapped with shimenawa ropes.

247.content: <Lunar veils(月之羽衣)> are pieces of cloth sewn with pure moonlight allowing the wearer to fly around freely, including through space.

248.content: <Ofuda(御札)> are talismans for purification, exorcism, or protection in Shinto religion.

249.content: <Onbashira(御柱)> are blessed wooden pillars that <Kanako(神奈子)> uses to fight, either as projectiles or as melee weapons.

250.comment: Chiyuri, Probability Space Hypervessel, Yumemi,千百合,可能性空间移动船,梦美
250.content: The <Probability Space Hypervessel(可能性空间移动船)> is a large ship that's capable of time travel. Its captain <Yumemi Okazaki(全名:冈崎梦美 简称:梦美)> and its lone crew member <Chiyuri Kitashirakawa(全名:北白河千百合 简称:千百合)> used this vessel to travel to Gensokyo in order to prove the existence of magic.

251.content: <Yama(阎魔)> are the judges of life and death of Gensokyo. They judge spirits ferried by <shinigami(死神)> across the <Sanzu River(三途河/三途川)>. Each <Yama(阎魔)> has a <rod of remorse(悔悟之棒)>.

252.content: Lord <Tsukuyomi(月夜见)> is the brother of Amaterasu and lord of the <Lunar Capital(月都/月之都)>. He is a few million years old.

253.content: Gensokyo's moon is like Earth, with green fields and lakes. <Lunarians(月人)> and <Moon Rabbits(月兔)> live in the safety of the <Lunar Capital(月都/月之都)>.

254.comment: Lunarian Capital, Lunar Capital,月都,月之都
254.content: The <Lunarian(月人)> Capital is a large city inhabited by the <lunarians(月人)> and <moon rabbits(月兔)>. Its technology and weaponry are far more advanced than the <Outside World(外界)>. It is located on the moon. The Lunar Defence Corps is it's military force. It is home to <Toyohime(丰姬)>, <Yorihime(依姬)>, <Rei'sen(铃仙二号/泠仙)>, <Sagume(探女)> and <Tsukuyomi(月夜见)>.

255.comment: Yorihime, Watatsuki,绵月依姬,绵月,依姬
255.content: <Watatsuki no Yorihime(全名:绵月依姬 简称:依姬)> is a <lunarian(月人)> princess and the younger sister of <Toyohime(丰姬)>. <Yorihime(依姬)> can borrow power from <gods(神)>, can absorb knowledge and is a superb swordswoman. <Yorihime(依姬)>'s strength and skills are unmatched by anyone in Gensokyo or the moon. Udongein was her pet and <Rei'sen(铃仙二号/泠仙)> is her current pet. <Yorihime(依姬)> respects <Eirin(永琳)> as her former teacher. <Yorihime(依姬)> is the leader of the Lunar Defense Corps, she is seen as stern and serious. <Yorihime(依姬)> has brown eyes and light purple hair tied into a ponytail with a yellow ribbon. She wears a white short-sleeved blouse with a dark red dress over it, golden bracelets, short red boots and a large belt.

256.content: <Rei'sen(铃仙二号/泠仙)> is a <moon rabbit(月兔)> and the pet of <Yorihime(依姬)> and <Toyohime(丰姬)>. She has the ability to teleport short distances. <Rei'sen(铃仙二号/泠仙)> was formerly a soldier of the Lunar Defense Corps. She is a little shy and easily intimidated. <Rei'sen(铃仙二号/泠仙)> has short light purple hair, red eyes and white fluffy bunny ears. She wears a black business suit, a white shirt, a red tie, a grey skirt, black kneesocks and loafers.

257.content: <Hell Ravens(地狱鸦)> are found in Hell where they help maintain the <Remains of Blazing Hell(灼热地狱遗址)>. They are humanoids with black wings and able to control fire, but are not <Tengu(天狗)>.

258.content: The <Sanzu River(三途河/三途川)> is where spirits cross over to the <Netherworld(冥界)> by paying a <shinigami(死神)>'s boat ride. <Komachi Onozuka(全名:小野塚小町 简称:小町)> is the ferrywoman. Only <Shinigami(死神)> and passengers can cross the river, everything else will sink and suffer a horrible fate.

259.content: <Senkai(仙界)> is an area similar to Gensokyo created <Toyosatomimi no Miko(全名:丰聪耳神子 简称:神子)> for her and her followers. It is a realm where <hermits(仙人)> can rest and meditate without being interrupted by others. It's accessed via the principle that any crack contains limitless space, which connects the world to any other location allowing it to be accessed from anywhere.

260.comment: Garden of the Sun,太阳花田
260.content: The <Garden of the Sun(太阳花田)> is located in the heart of Gensokyo. Sunflowers are everywhere in the Garden. Lots of <youkai(妖怪)> and <fairies(妖精)> gather at this spot for concerts or for flower viewing. It's hard to leave the Garden. In the middle of the garden lies <Mugenkan(梦幻馆)>. <Yuuka(幽香)>, <Elly(艾丽)> and <Eternity Larva(全名:爱塔妮缇拉尔瓦 简称:拉尔瓦/爱塔妮缇)> can be found here.

261.content: The <Ruins of Vina(维纳的废墟)> are located somewhere in <Makai(魔界)>. It used to be a giant castle but now it houses a <demon(魔界人)> known as <Elis(全名:依莉斯)>.

262.comment: Forest, Forest of Magic,魔法森林,魔法之森,森林
262.content: The <Forest of Magic(魔法森林)> is located near the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>. Many <magicians(魔法使)> live in this forest for the sake of increasing their magical powers with hallucinogenic mushrooms, and it is home to many repulsive things. Ignoring the dangerous environment, it's both a safe and secretive place to seclude oneself, or a fairly nice place to live for people who don't like to be disturbed. <Marisa(魔理沙)>, <Alice(爱丽丝)> and Rinnosuke all live in the <Forest of Magic(魔法森林)>.

263.content: The <Dream World(梦境世界)> is a world of dreams ruled by the <baku(獏/貘)>. You have to be asleep in order to reach it. <Doremy(全名:哆来咪)> Sweet lives here.

264.comment: Rabbit, Earth Rabbit,兔子,兔,地球兔,妖怪兔
264.content: Earth rabbits are natives of Gensokyo often wielding great magic capabilities and the ability to transform into either a rabbit or a girl with rabbit ears. <Tewi(帝/天为)> leads the earth rabbits. They live in the <Bamboo Forest of the Lost(迷途竹林)>. They have allied themselves with the residents of <Eientei(永远庭)> and work there.

265.content: <Nue(鵺)> are chimera-like <youkai(妖怪)> and extremely rare in Gensokyo. They are able to make themselves and other objects unrecognizable to the point that they looks like something completely different.

266.comment: Wind God's Lake,风神之湖,八坂之湖
266.content: <Wind God's Lake(风神之湖)> is located on top of the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>, next to <Moriya Shrine(守矢神社)>. It has holy properties.

267.content: The <Canal of Willows(柳之运河)> is a forest of willow trees located near the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>. It's said to be peaceful as there are rarely any <youkai(妖怪)> wandering the area.

268.content: <Higan(彼岸)> is on the other side of the <Sanzu River(三途河/三途川)>. <Higan(彼岸)> has no night or day, no weather, and no seasons. It is an endless expanse of flowers with gentle warmth. <Higan(彼岸)> is a place where departed souls are judged by <Eiki Shiki(全名:四季映姬 简称:映姬)>. <Komachi Onozuka(全名:小野塚小町 简称:小町)> lives here. <Kutaka Niwatari(全名:庭渡久侘歌 简称:久侘歌)> works here as the gatekeeper.

269.content: <Mayohiga(迷途之家)> is an abandoned village located near the <Great Hakurei Barrier(博丽大结界)> somewhere in the mountains. <Humans(人类)> tend to stumble across it when they try to leave Gensokyo without using the <Hakurei Shrine(博丽神社)>. Taking something from <Mayohiga(迷途之家)> gives good luck. Cats live in <Mayohiga(迷途之家)> because <Chen(全名:橙)> brings them there.

270.comment: Kakashi Spirit News, Hatate, Himekaidou,姬海棠果,姬海棠羽立,姬海棠极,姬海棠,果,极,羽立,花果子念报
270.content: <Hatate Himekaidou(全名:姬海棠果/姬海棠羽立/姬海棠极 简称:果/羽立/极)> is a <crow tengu(鸦天狗)> living on <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. She can use spirit photography to see things from somewhere else. Her articles are less sensationalist than <Aya(文文)>'s, who is her rival. <Hatate(果/羽立/极)> is really lazy but chipper and friendly. She is a shut in and rarely leaves home. <Hatate(果/羽立/极)> has brown eyes and brown hair in pigtails with purple ribbons. She wears a pink shirt with a frilly collar, black tie, a purple tokin, a checkered purple and black skirt, and geta sandals.

271.comment: Mamizou, Futatsuiwa,二岩猯藏,二岩,猯藏
271.content: <Mamizou Futatsuiwa(全名:二岩猯藏 简称:猯藏)> is a <bake-danuki(妖怪狸)>. She can disguise herself or things around her. <Mamizou(猯藏)> is mischievous but good-natured and quite responsible. She lives in the <Tanuki Forest(妖怪狸之森)>, is a guest of the <Myouren Temple(命莲寺)> and a friend of <Nue(鵺)>. She lends money to poor <humans(人类)>. <Mamizou(猯藏)> has brown eyes, light brown shoulder-length hair, tanuki ears, and a giant, fluffy striped tail. She wears a green leaf on her head, and glasses. <Mamizou(猯藏)> wears a pink shirt with a leather apron, a skirt striped like her tail, and carries a bottle of sake.

272.content: <Hakugyokurou(白玉楼)> is a <ghost(亡灵)> shrine located in the <Netherworld(冥界)>. The <youkai(妖怪)> cherry tree <Saigyou Ayakashi(西行妖)> is dormant in its gardens. Hakugyoukurou is the home of <Yuyuko(幽幽子)> and <Youmu(妖梦)>.

273.content: The <Youkai(妖怪)> <Tanuki Forest(妖怪狸之森)> is located near the <Human Village(人类村落/人间之里)>. The <Youkai(妖怪)> <Tanuki Forest(妖怪狸之森)> houses all sorts of <youkai(妖怪)> and tanuki. <Mamizou Futatsuiwa(全名:二岩猯藏 简称:猯藏)> can be seen around there.

274.content: The <Lake of Blood(血之湖)> is a lake in the mountains that appears to be filled with pure blood, rather than water. Within it lies the entrance to <Mugenkan(梦幻馆)>. <Kurumi(胡桃)> is the gatekeeper of the entrance to the lake. <Elly(艾丽)> stands guard within the lake, at the border between Gensokyo and the Fantasy World, protecting the entrance to <Mugenkan(梦幻馆)>.

key: 莉莉卡 普莉兹姆利巴
275.comment: Lyrica,莉莉卡 普莉兹姆利巴,莉莉卡,普莉兹姆利巴
275.content: <Lyrica Prismriver(全名:莉莉卡普莉兹姆利巴 简称:莉莉卡)> is a <poltergeist(骚灵)> keyboardist and the third Prismriver sister. Her music enhances the effect of <Merlin(梅露兰)>'s and <Lunasa(露娜萨)>'s. She lazy and crafty. <Lyrica(莉莉卡)> has brown eyes and short light brown hair. Her red keyboard is always nearby. She wears red clothing dress with pink and black trimming over a white shirt, red shorts, and a red hat with a green star decoration. She's the shortest Prismriver sister.

276.comment: Mai, Teireida,丁礼田舞,丁礼田,舞
276.content: <Mai Teireida(全名:丁礼田舞 简称:舞)> is an immortal <human(人类)>. <Mai(舞)> can increase a person's physical energy by dancing behind them. She lives in the Land of the Backdoor, working for <Okina(隐岐奈)> with her partner <Satono(里乃)>. <Mai(舞)> is scatterbrained and impulsive but serves <Okina(隐岐奈)> unquestioningly. She has short dull green hair with two long side locks, and green eyes. <Mai(舞)> wears a kazaori-eboshi, a green dress with short sleeves, a white half apron and collar with red frills and a yellow bow, black kneesocks, and green shoes. She holds a bamboo stalk.

277.comment: Land of the Back Door,后户之国
277.content: The <Land of the Back Door(后户之国)> is a dimension ruled and created by <Okina(隐岐奈)>. It's filled with floating doors that can lead to any location in Gensokyo. <Satono(里乃)> and <Mai(舞)> live there.

278.content: The <Nameless Hill(无名之丘)> is located on the opposite side of the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)> and halfway up a small mountain. It is a meadow filled with purple and white lilies-of-the-valley which are poisonous. <Medicine Melancholy(全名:梅蒂欣梅兰可莉 简称:梅蒂欣)> lives there.

279.comment: Japan, Outside World, Earth,日本,外界,外面的世界,地球
279.content: The <Outside World(外界)> is modern-day Earth, which is separate from Gensokyo. It is technologically advanced but lacks <faith(信仰)> and belief. Gensokyo is closest in culture to old Japan.

280.comment: Nuclear Furnace,核聚变炉,核融合炉
280.content: The <Nuclear Furnace(核聚变炉/核融合炉)> is located in the deepest parts of the <Underworld(地底)>. It creates nuclear fusion energy for power and heat. <Kanako(神奈子)> and <Suwako(诹访子)> built the <Nuclear Furnace(核聚变炉/核融合炉)>. Utsuho powers it.

281.comment: Underground Geyser Center,间歇泉地下中心
281.content: The <Underground Geyser Center(间歇泉地下中心)> is a research facility and located in the deepest parts of the <Underworld(地底)>. It is connected to the <Nuclear Furnace(核聚变炉/核融合炉)>. <Kappa(河童)> and the <gods(神)> of the <Moriya Shrine(守矢神社)> use it for research.

282.content: The <Shining Needle Castle(辉针城)> is located in the sky near <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. It was created by the <Miracle Mallet(万宝槌)> a long time ago. It is the home to <Shinmyoumaru(针妙丸)> and other <inchlings(小人)>.

283.content: <Eientei(永远庭)> is a traditional Japanese mansion located in the <Bamboo Forest(迷途竹林)>. Its corridors sprawl endlessly. <Kaguya(辉夜)> is its mistress. It includes a clinic where <Eirin(永琳)> works. It is home to <Reisen(铃仙)> & <Tewi(帝/天为)>.

284.comment: Kasodani, Kyouko,幽谷响子,幽谷,响子
284.content: <Kyouko Kasodani(全名:幽谷响子 简称:响子)> is a <yamabiko(山彦)>. She can reflect sounds. She is a Buddhist priestess-in-training at the <Myouren Temple(命莲寺)> and in a band with <Mystia(米斯蒂娅)>. <Kyouko(响子)> is cheerful, dutiful, and energetic but has a bit of a rebellious streak. She has teal hair and teal eyes along with brown dog ears. <Kyouko(响子)> wears a long pale pink dress with teal flower ornaments, a white dress under it with a black trim, and black shoes. She has a short tail and carries a bamboo broom.

285.comment: Myouren Temple, Palanquin Ship,命莲寺,圣辇船
285.content: The <Myouren Temple(命莲寺)> was originally a ship. It rests atop the Hall of Dream's Great Mausoleum and has been turned in a Buddhist Temple. It is also called the "<Palanquin Ship(圣辇船)>." <Byakuren(圣白莲)> can make it fly. This is the home of <Byakuren(圣白莲)>, <Shou(守矢神社)>, <Nazrin(娜兹玲)>, <Ichirin(一轮)>, <Murasa(村纱)>, <Nue(鵺)>, <Kyouko(响子)> and <Mamizou(猯藏)>. Koishi and Jo'on can be found here occasionally.

286.comment: Kirisame, Marisa,雾雨,魔理沙,雾雨魔理沙
286.content: <Marisa Kirisame(全名:雾雨魔理沙 简称:魔理沙)> is a <human(人类)> witch. She uses heat and light magic and receives power from the <mini-hakkero(迷你八卦炉)>. She lives in the Kirisame household in the <Forest of Magic(魔法森林)>. <Marisa(魔理沙)> enjoys finding mushrooms and stealing things she finds interesting. She is outgoing, informal, and loves action. <Marisa(魔理沙)> is friends with <Nitori(荷取)>, <Alice(爱丽丝)> and <Patchouli(帕秋莉)>. <Reimu(灵梦)> is <Marisa(魔理沙)>'s best friend. <Marisa(魔理沙)>'s signature attack is "<Master Spark(极限火花)>". <Marisa(魔理沙)> has blonde hair and yellow eyes. She wears a black vest and skirt, white apron and shirt. <Marisa(魔理沙)> has a black witch hat with white ribbons, and flies on a magic broom.

287.content: The <Genbu Ravine(玄武涧/玄武之泽)> is located near <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)> and <Forest of Magic(魔法森林)>. The bottom looks like turtleshell. It's surrounded by six-sided cliffs, and a waterfall drops into a lake at the bottom. <Nitori(荷取)> lives near the Ravine.

288.content: The <Animal Realm(畜生界)> is a skyscraper-filled metropolis located in Hell, with a forest known as the <Primate Spirit Garden(灵长园)>. The <Animal Realm(畜生界)> is filled with animal spirits and is a harsh environment relying on survival of the fittest. The animal spirits rule, and enslave <human(人类)> spirits. Notable leaders are <Yachie(八千慧)> and <Saki(骊驹早鬼)>.

289.comment: Land of Fantasy, Eastern Wonderland, Land of Illusions, Gensoukyo, Gensokyo,幻想乡
289.content: Gensokyo is a place located somewhere around the Yatsugatake Mountains in Japan. It's a land of illusions: it is hidden from the <Outside World(外界)>, and surrounded by the <Great Hakurei Barrier(博丽大结界)>. Gensokyo's inhabitants are mainly creatures of Japanese Folklore and <humans(人类)>. Gensokyo is surrounded by <Great Hakurei Barrier(博丽大结界)>. Everyone speaks Modern Japanese. The technology in Gensokyo is similar to 1880s-era Japan.

290.comment: Great Mausoleum, Hall of Dreams,梦殿大祀庙
290.content: The Hall of Dreams' Great Mausoleum is located under the <Myouren Temple(命莲寺)> and is entered through a cave. It was the tomb of <Toyosatomimi no Miko(全名:丰聪耳神子 简称:神子)> where she was sealed by Buddhist monks, but now serves as her home for her and her followers.

291.content: Rods of Remorse are carried by every <Yama(阎魔)>. It is used to beat sinners until they repent.

292.comment: Shikieiki, Shiki, Yama, Enma, Eiki,四季,映姬,夜摩仙那度,四季映姬,四季映姬 夜摩仙那度,阎魔
292.content: <Eiki Shiki(全名:四季映姬 简称:映姬)> is a <Yama(阎魔)> living in <Higan(彼岸)>. <Eiki(映姬)> is the Judge of the Dead for the <Ministry of Right and Wrong(是非曲直厅)>. She has power to judge others using the <Rod of Remorse(悔悟之棒)> and the <Cleansed Crystal Mirror(净玻璃之镜)>. <Yuyuko(幽幽子)> is <Eiki(映姬)>'s subordinate. <Eiki(映姬)> often scolds her servant <Komachi(小町)>. <Eiki(映姬)> serves <Hecatia(赫卡提亚)>. She is known to scold and lecture others, but does so with goodwill. <Eiki(映姬)> has short green hair swept to the right and blue eyes. She wears a blue and white hat with a gold emblem, a blue and black uniform, and black shoes with red bows.

293.comment: Enma, Ministry of Right and Wrong,是非曲直厅,阎魔
293.content: The <Ministry of Right and Wrong(是非曲直厅)> is the organization that manages the afterlife. They decide who goes to <Heaven(天界)> or Hell. <Hecatia Lapislazuli(全名:赫卡提亚 拉碧斯拉祖利 简称:赫卡提亚)> is the leader of Ministry. <Eiki(映姬)> judges the souls of those who died and the <Kishin(鬼神)> hunt those who live too long.

294.comment: Iku, Nagae,永江衣玖,永江,衣玖
294.content: <Iku Nagae(全名:永江衣玖 简称:衣玖)> is an oarfish <youkai(妖怪)>. <Iku(衣玖)> has the power to read the mood of a place and perfectly adapt to it. She can cause storms using the <Dragon God(龙神)>'s power. <Iku(衣玖)> is the envoy of the <Dragon(龙)> Palace and lives in <Heaven(天界)>. She is loyal to <celestials(天人)> and <Dragon(龙)> Palace residents, and is <Tenshi(天子)>'s friend. <Iku(衣玖)> is focused on her duties and is rather calm and businesslike. <Iku(衣玖)> has red eyes and blue hair. She wears a white and red frilly shirt, a long black skirt, and a black round hat with a very long red ribbon. <Iku(衣玖)> has a long white and red shawl along her arms and chest.

295.content: <Nazrin(娜兹玲)> is a mouse <youkai(妖怪)>. She can find anything she is tasked to look for. She lives in a shack on the <Nameless Hill(无名之丘)> and leads a large flock of mice. <Nazrin(娜兹玲)> a skilled dowser, but is full of herself and easily frightened. She was sent by <Bishamonten(毘沙门天)> to watch over <Shou(守矢神社)> and her Pagoda. <Nazrin(娜兹玲)> has short gray hair and red eyes, mouse ears and a thick mouse tail. She wears a black sleeveless dress with rectangular cutouts at the bottom, a white undershirt and a dull blue capelet. <Nazrin(娜兹玲)> wears black slippers, a crystal pendant, and carries two dowsing rods.

296.comment: Deep Road to Hell,地狱的深道
296.content: The <Deep Road to Hell(地狱的深道)> leads to <Former Hell(旧地狱)>. It's green and gloomy. <Parsee(帕露西)> roams around here.

297.content: The <Fantastic Blowhole(幻想风穴)> is a location in the <Underworld(地底)> near the <Deep Road to Hell(地狱的深道)>. It's a cave that is always wet with a very strong wind. <Kisume(琪斯美)> and <Yamame(山女)> live there.

298.content: <Chang'e(全名:嫦娥)> is a <lunarian(月人)> who was the mistress of all <moon rabbits(月兔)>. She is now a prisoner on the moon for her entire immortal lifetime after drinking the <Hourai Elixir(蓬莱药)>. <Junko(纯狐)> has a major grudge against <Chang'e(全名:嫦娥)> for killing <Junko(纯狐)>'s son. <Hecatia Lapislazuli(全名:赫卡提亚 拉碧斯拉祖利 简称:赫卡提亚)> has a grudge against <Chang'e(全名:嫦娥)> since <Chang'e(全名:嫦娥)>'s husband destroyed the suns that balanced the darkness of Hell.

299.comment: Hot Spring Town,温泉街,旧地狱温泉街
299.content: <Hot Spring Town(旧地狱温泉街)> is a resort in <Former Hell(旧地狱)>. It is accessible from the <Rainbow Cavern(地灵虹洞/虹洞)> of Earth Spirits, and managed by <Yuugi(勇仪)>. <Hot Spring Town(旧地狱温泉街)> has densely packed traditional Japanese houses. Hot steamy water constantly pours from up above. There are large hot springs everywhere, which <oni(鬼)> and vengeful spirits use to bathe.

300.comment: Sanae, Kochiya,东风谷早苗,东风谷,早苗
300.content: <Sanae Kochiya(全名:东风谷早苗 简称:早苗)> is a shrine maiden. She can perform miracles and can summon <Suwako(诹访子)> or <Kanako(神奈子)>. <Sanae(早苗)> is confident, energetic, and dutiful. She considers <Reimu(灵梦)> her rival, but also a friend. <Sanae(早苗)> lives at and tends to the <Moriya shrine(守矢神社)>. She has green eyes, and long green hair. <Sanae(早苗)> wears a white and blue shrine maiden outfit with detached sleeves. She has a frog pin, and a long white snake decoration in her hair. <Sanae(早苗)> also wears white kneesocks and black loafers. She is a descendant of <Suwako(诹访子)>.

301.comment: Bunbunmaru, Aya, Shameimaru,射命丸文,射命丸,文,文文,文文。新闻,文文新闻
301.content: <Aya Shameimaru(全名:射命丸文 简称:文/文文)> is a <crow tengu(鸦天狗)> reporter. She has power to manipulate wind. <Aya(文文)> is one of the strongest <tengu(天狗)>, and one of the fastest. <Aya(文文)> lives somewhere on <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. She always looks for gossip, relying on aggressive reporting tactics and is prone to exaggerate. While <Aya(文文)> actually cares about the truth, she is somewhat full of herself. <Aya(文文)> runs a newspaper called the <Bunbunmaru(文文。新闻)>. She is <Hatate(果/羽立/极)>'s rival. <Aya(文文)> has red eyes and shoulder-length black hair. She wears a white blouse with a black ribbon, black skirt, red geta sandals and a red tokin. She usually carries a camera.

302.content: <Bake-danuki(妖怪狸)> are <youkai(妖怪)> tanuki. They have the ability to transform and disguise themselves as objects or other species. <Bake-danuki(妖怪狸)> can also transform leaves into other objects.

303.content: <Were-hakutaku(白泽/半白泽)> are <humans(人类)> with the ability to turn into a <hakutaku(白泽/半白泽)> on a full moon. <Hakutaku(白泽/半白泽)> are bovine <youkai(妖怪)> who bring good fortune and give sage advice.

304.content: <Hakurouken(白楼剑)> is an ancestral wakizashi of the Konpaku family. Only Konpaku family members can wield it. <Youmu(妖梦)> owns it. It erases doubt from <humans(人类)> on attack. <Ghosts(亡灵)> achieve nirvana when cut by <Hakurouken(白楼剑)>.

305.content: Jiang shi are zombie <youkai(妖怪)> that move by hopping around and can turn other <humans(人类)> into Jiang Shi by biting them. The zombification will only be permanent if the bite is fatal. They have stiff limbs and cannot think for themselves, usually following a master.

306.comment: Barrier of Life and Death,幽明结界
306.content: The <Barrier of Life and Death(幽明结界)> is located in the sky and separates Gensokyo and the <Netherworld(冥界)>. It takes the shape of a colossal door.

307.content: The <Spring Path(春之小径)> is a long mysterious path full of flowers and cherry blossom located near <Misty Lake(雾之湖)> and the <Forest of Magic(魔法森林)>.

308.comment: Chiyuri, Kitashirakawa,北白河,千百合,北白河千百合
308.content: <Chiyuri Kitashirakawa(全名:北白河千百合 简称:千百合)> is a <human(人类)> not native to Gensokyo. She can use artificial magic, is a bit excitable, and will often make situations much worse than they already are. <Chiyuri(千百合)> has blonde hair and yellow eyes. She wears a white sailor uniform with a shade of blue which looks too small for her and a blue neckerchief. <Chiyuri(千百合)> commands the <Probability Space Hypervessel(可能性空间移动船)>. She assists <Yumemi Okazaki(全名:冈崎梦美 简称:梦美)>.

309.content: <Former Hell(旧地狱)> is a region in the <Underworld(地底)> that used to be Hell. Due to overpopulation, the <Yama(阎魔)> moved Hell to a different location. It is accessed by the <Deep Road to Hell(地狱的深道)>, guarded by <Parsee(帕露西)>. The <Palace of the Earth Spirits(地灵殿)> is found here. This place is the home of <Yuugi(勇仪)>, <Satori(觉)>, Koishi, Utsuho, and Rin.

310.content: <Hisoutensoku(非想天则)> is a nuclear powered mecha created by the <kappa(河童)>. It resembles a giant golden robot. It is used for advertising the Future Water <Youkai(妖怪)> Bazaar, but is often confused for all sorts of monsters.

311.content: The <Road of Liminality(中有之道)> is located at the back of the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)> and is connected to the <Sanzu River(三途河/三途川)>. Harmless <ghosts(亡灵)> roam around, and both <youkai(妖怪)> and <humans(人类)> built stands to sell their wares here.

312.content: The <Primate Spirit Garden(灵长园)> is a large park resembling a kofun burial mound, located in the <Animal Realm(畜生界)>. Part of it was transformed into a high-tech fortress by <Keiki Haniyasushin(全名:埴安神袿姬 简称:袿姬)>. The animal spirits are trying to take back this region but are unable to defeat the <Haniwa Army Corps(埴轮兵团)> defending it. <Keiki(袿姬)> and <Mayumi(磨弓)> live here.

313.content: The <Jeweled Pagoda(毘沙门天的宝塔/毘沙门天/宝塔)> of <Bishamonten(毘沙门天)> is a spherical gem held in a pagoda-shaped case. It is owned and used by <Shou(守矢神社)>. It can fire powerful laser beams. If shot at the ground, it will turn it into gems.

314.content: The <Great Youkai Forest(妖怪的树海)> is located at the base of the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. It's a forest known to block out sunlight allowing most <youkai(妖怪)> to live there in peace.

315.content: <Matenshi(魔天使)> is an angel residing in <Makai(魔界)>. She has purple hair at medium length and purple eyes. <Matenshi(魔天使)> wears a blue dress with a blue apron that has a white cross design on it. She also has angel-like wings. She is known to be hostile to <humans(人类)>.

316.comment: Prismriver, Prismriver Sisters,普莉兹姆利巴,骚灵三姐妹,普莉兹姆利巴姐妹
316.content: The <Prismriver Sisters(骚灵三姐妹)> are <Lunasa(露娜萨)>, <Merlin(梅露兰)> and <Lyrica(莉莉卡)>. They form "the <Phantom(幽灵)> Ensemble". The <Prismriver Sisters(骚灵三姐妹)> play concerts throughout Gensokyo. They live in the Ruined Western Mansion with <Layla(蕾拉)>.

317.comment: Hakugyokurou, Saigyou Ayakashi,白玉楼,西行妖
317.content: <Saigyou Ayakashi(西行妖)> is a <youkai(妖怪)> cherry tree living in <Hakugyokurou(白玉楼)>. The <Saigyou Ayakashi(西行妖)> has a lot of dead bodies buried under it to seal its cherry blossoms. It drains life from those under its canopy. If it blooms, it will cause mass death.

318.content: <Roukanken(楼观剑)> is a long-bladed katana created by <youkai(妖怪)> and wielded by <Youmu Konpaku(全名:魂魄妖梦 简称:妖梦)>. <Youmu(妖梦)> likes to boast about the power of this sword, usually exclaiming "The things that cannot be cut by my <Roukanken(楼观剑)>, forged by <youkai(妖怪)>, are close to none!". Supposedly, it can kill ten spirits with one stroke. The sheath is decorated with a flower and <ofuda(御札)>.

319.content: The <Soul Torch(人魂灯)> is a small paper lantern which attracts <phantoms(幽灵)> when lit. It is used by <Yuyuko Saigyouji(全名:西行寺幽幽子 简称:幽幽子)>. She can light or extinguish the torch from any distance.

320.content: The <Miracle Mallet(万宝槌)> is a magical tool wielded by <Shinmyoumaru(针妙丸)>. The <Miracle Mallet(万宝槌)> can change the size of anything with its powers or grant the wielder's wish at the cost proportional to the scale of the wish. The <Miracle Mallet(万宝槌)> can only be wielded by the <inchlings(小人)>.

321.content: The <Sword of Hisou(绯想之剑)> looks like a burning-red jian. It is wielded by <Tenshi Hinanawi(全名:比那名居天子 简称:天子)>. It has the power to identify one's spirit, can cut through anything and use spirit energy. It can only be used and summoned by <Tenshi(天子)>.

322.comment: Kishin, Sagume,稀神探女,稀神,探女
322.content: <Sagume Kishin(全名:稀神探女 简称:探女)> is a <lunarian(月人)> <divine spirit(神灵)>. Her ability reverses the course of any situation she speaks about. She speaks very little because of her ability, but is sharp and logical. <Sagume(探女)> has red eyes, short light grey hair with a princess braid around her head and a single angel wing on her back. She wears a purple dress whose bottom cuts off in an arrow pattern, a red microphone bowtie, a tan jacket with black alchemical symbols, and brown shoes.

323.comment: Toyohime, Watatsuki no Toyohime, Watatsuki,绵月丰姬,绵月,丰姬
323.content: <Watatsuki no Toyohime(全名:绵月丰姬 简称:丰姬)> is a <lunarian(月人)> princess and older sister of <Yorihime(依姬)>. <Toyohime(丰姬)> possesses incommensurate luck, power, and can manipulate the physical and conceptual boundaries of the Moon and Earth, as well as mountains and seas. <Toyohime(丰姬)> has a gentle personality but is rather aloof. Udongein was her pet and <Rei'sen(铃仙二号/泠仙)> is her current pet. <Toyohime(丰姬)> respects <Eirin(永琳)> as her former teacher. She has long flowing blonde hair and golden eyes. <Toyohime(丰姬)> wears a white long-sleeved blouse with a blue dress over it, a loose belt, short purple boots and a white mobcap with a purple ribbon. She wields a fan that can purify things to the atomic level.

324.content: <Unzan(云山)> is a <nyuudou(入道)> or enlightened spirit who follows and guards <Ichirin(一轮)>. He can make his fists grow to a massive size or shoot <danmaku(弹幕)>. <Unzan(云山)> takes the appearance of a pinkish cloud with the face of an angry old man, but he is quite shy and prefers that <Ichirin(一轮)> speak on his behalf. Even then, he gives her insight when needed.

325.content: The <Grassroots Youkai(草根妖怪网络)> Network is a loose group of weaker and more docile <youkai(妖怪)>. They help each other and trade information.

326.comment: Mike, Goutokuji,豪德寺三花,豪德寺,三花
326.content: <Mike Goutokuji(全名:豪德寺三花)> is a female calico <Maneki-Neko(招财猫)>. She has the power to bring either money or customers to a shop, but not both at once. She lives near <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. Mike loves haggling but prefers lazing around. She was rejected by other <Maneki-Neko(招财猫)> because she is a calico. Mike has short brown-<orange(奥莲姬)>-white hair, a cat tail and cat ears, and <orange(奥莲姬)> eyes. She wears a white shirt and skirt with brown and <orange(奥莲姬)> patches, leather bracelets and a choker with a gold bell. Mike carries a good luck koban coin and is barefoot.

327.content: <Maneki-nekos(招财猫)> are catpeople that bring good fortune to businesses. They are usually pure white but exceptions exist and are often rejected by the others.

328.content: <Yamawaro(山童)> are similar to <Kappa(河童)> but live in mountainous areas and thick forests rather than near bodies of water. They are rivals with <Kappas(河童)>. <Yamawaros(山童)> depend on <Kappa(河童)> technology but are better businesspeople.

329.comment: Yamashiro, Takane,山城,高岭,山城高岭
329.content: <Takane Yamashiro(全名:山城高岭 简称:高岭)> is a <yamawaro(山童)> living in the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>'s forests. She has the ability to manipulate the Qi of the forest. Takane is more amiable than average <yamawaro(山童)>, and a good businesswoman. She is wary of <humans(人类)> but manages the <Moriya Shrine(守矢神社)> cable car. Takane has fluffy shoulder-length green hair and dark green eyes. She wears a dark green camouflage dress with many pouches, a dark blue camo cap and brown boots. Takane carries a briefcase on her back with the key around her neck.

330.comment: Komakusa, Sannyo,驹草,山如,驹草山如
330.content: <Sannyo Komakusa(全名:驹草山如)> or Komakusa-dayuu is a <yamajorou(山女郎)>. She can manipulate minds with her pipe's smoke. Sannyo owns a gambling den on the <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>. She is blunt and rough-spoken and a skilled manipulator. Sannyo has purple hair in a ponytail tied with a yellow bow, and red eyes. Sannyo wears a lavish purple kimono dress, a red vest with gold filigree and geta sandals. She carries a golden fan and a <dragon(龙)>-shaped smoking pipe.

331.comment: Tamatsukuri, Misumaru,玉造,魅须丸,玉造魅须丸
331.content: <Misumaru(魅须丸)> Tamatsukuri is a <god(神)>. She can craft magatama from <dragon(龙)> gems and rare magical minerals. Her power lets her store abilities, emotions and memories in magatama. She crafted <Reimu(灵梦)>'s <Yin-yang orbs(阴阳玉)>. <Misumaru(魅须丸)> cares deeply about people and the environment. <Misumaru(魅须丸)> has brown eyes and blonde and brown hair with a headband and hair ties decorated with <dragon(龙)> gems. She wears a red shirt with a purple vine pattern and white puffy sleeves, a yellow dress with a green vine pattern and a purple sash. <Misumaru(魅须丸)>'s clothing is decorated with many rainbow magatama. She is barefoot.

332.content: <Tsukasa Kudamaki(全名:菅牧典 简称:典)> is a kuda-gitsune. She can use her power to find weak spots in people's souls. <Tsukasa(典)> is trusted by many for her useful advice but is highly manipulative and mean-spirited. She is <Megumu(饭纲丸龙)>'s right-hand woman. She has neck-length blonde hair,yellow eyes, blonde fox ears with white tips and a fox tail. <Tsukasa(典)> wears a short white cheongsam with mint green laces and a plant design, white tabi socks and carries a test tube around.

333.comment: Iizunamaru, Megumu,饭纲丸,龙,饭纲丸龙
333.content: <Megumu Iizunamaru(全名:饭纲丸龙)> is a <great tengu(大天狗)>. She can manipulate the starry sky. She is one of the leaders of <Youkai Mountain(妖怪之山)>'s <tengu(天狗)>. She speaks respectfully but cares only for her position in the <tengu(天狗)> hierarchy. <Tsukasa(典)> and <Chimata(千亦)> are her associates. <Megumu(饭纲丸龙)> has dark blue hair and red eyes. She wears a blue dress, a black coat with a jeweled gold pauldron and white puffs at the bottom, a blue tokin hat, black socks & purple geta sandals. She wields a camera tripod as a bludgeon.

334.comment: Chimata, Tenkyuu,天弓,千亦,天弓千亦
334.content: <Chimata Tenkyuu(全名:天弓千亦 简称:千亦)> is a <god(神)> of the marketplace. She can transfer the ownership of things from one person to another, including concepts or abilities. <Chimata(千亦)> is polite but somewhat dramatic in her behavior, and very strung up on the rules of barter market. She hates profit-seekers, preferring those who wish to share the value of things. She is <Megumu(饭纲丸龙)>'s and <Tsukasa(典)>'s associate. Her eyes and hair look like a dark sky. She wears a dress with sections of all colors of the rainbow connected by zippers, magenta boots and a cape whose inside looks like daytime sky.

335.comment: Himemushi, Momoyo,姬虫,百百世,姬虫百百世
335.content: <Momoyo Himemushi(全名:姬虫百百世)> is an oomukade. Her ability lets her devour <dragons(龙)>. She lives in the Rainbow <Dragon(龙)> Cave and mines <Dragon(龙)> Gems. Momoyo is incomprehensibly strong and emits deadly toxins, and thus respects anyone who dares approach her. Momoyo speaks in a very masculine manner. She works for <Megumu(饭纲丸龙)>. Momoyo has very messy gray hair and eyes. She wears a black shirt and skirt with gold swirls lined with many jade rings. Momoyo has many <orange(奥莲姬)> ribbons tied around her arms and legs, an <orange(奥莲姬)> sash around her waist and is barefoot. She carries a golden shovel and pickaxe.

336.content: <Tokiko(朱鹭子)> is a crested ibis <youkai(妖怪)>. She is weak and has no special abilities. <Tokiko(朱鹭子)> is curious and loves to read, often visiting places with large amounts of books. She has white hair with a blue front tuft and side bangs, small pointy blue horns, and red eyes. She wears a blue and black gothic dress with wide white sleeves, a large blue ribbon and black boots.

337.comment: Child of Miare, Akyuu,御阿礼之子,阿求
337.content: The <Child of Miare(御阿礼之子)> is the reincarnation of Hieda no Are and the keeper of Gensokyo's knowledge. They live for a very short time but keep memories of their previous lives and are unable to forget things they see.

338.comment: Toutetsu, Yuuma,饕餮,尤魔,饕餮尤魔
338.content: <Yuuma Toutetsu(全名:饕餮尤魔 简称:尤魔)> is a <Taotie(饕餮)>. She has the ability to swallow anything and absorb it, and can also "eat" attacks. <Yuuma(尤魔)> is the head of the <Gouyoku(刚欲同盟)> Alliance, and a rival of <Saki(骊驹早鬼)> and <Yachie(八千慧)>. <Yuuma(尤魔)> lives in the <Animal Realm(畜生界)> and visits the <Sea of Petroleum(石油之海)> and <Abandoned Hell of Blood Pools(旧血池地狱)> for power. <Yuuma(尤魔)> is greedy and opportunistic. <Yuuma(尤魔)> has fluffy white hair like wool, and slitted red sheep eyes. She has long, pointy ears with gold earrings, and big red ram horns decorated with blue ribbons. <Yuuma(尤魔)> wears a blue dress with white patterns similar to Chinese bronzework and short red sleeves with exposed shoulders, a bronze talisman around her neck, and is barefoot. <Yuuma(尤魔)> carries a massive spoon she uses as a weapon.

339.content: The <Gouyoku(刚欲同盟)> Alliance is an organization in the <Animal Realm(畜生界)> led by <Yuuma Toutetsu(全名:饕餮尤魔 简称:尤魔)> and a rival to <Yachie(八千慧)> and <Saki(骊驹早鬼)>'s organizations. They represent greed.

340.content: The <Sea of Petroleum(石油之海)> is a location in Hell which is filled with oil. It connects to the <Abandoned Hell of Blood Pools(旧血池地狱)>. <Yuuma Toutetsu(全名:饕餮尤魔 简称:尤魔)> frequents it to acquire power.

341.comment: Abandoned Hell of Blood Pools,旧血池地狱
341.content: The <Abandoned Hell of Blood Pools(旧血池地狱)> is a <former Hell(旧地狱)> that contains pools that represents different sins. <Yuuma Toutetsu(全名:饕餮尤魔 简称:尤魔)> uses these pools to power herself up.

342.content: A <Taotie(饕餮)> is a type of evil beast in Chinese mythology. They have sheeplike features and are creatures of corruption and greed.

343.content: The <Rainbow Cavern(地灵虹洞/虹洞)> of Earth Spirits is an underground passage located in the <Forest of Magic(魔法森林)>, leading to the <Hot Spring Town(旧地狱温泉街)> in <Former Hell(旧地狱)>. <Yamame(山女)> sometimes lurks around.

344.content: <Yukari(紫)>, <Okina(隐岐奈)> and <Kasen(华扇)> are the currently known sages of Gensokyo, and help maintain the <Great Hakurei Barrier(博丽大结界)>.

345.content: The Sorcerer's Sutra Scroll is an infinite scroll that only <Hijiri(圣白莲)> <Byakuren(圣白莲)> can wield. It contains an unlimited amount of spells and does not deteriorate. It can cast spells on its own, or enhance <Hijiri(圣白莲)>'s.

346.content: Omukade are <youkai(妖怪)> giant centipedes. Oomukade live under mountains and reach colossal sizes. They are rumored to be <dragon(龙)>-eaters and are assumed to be tremendously strong as a result.

347.content: The Shining Needle Sword is a magical needle used by <Shinmyoumaru(针妙丸)>. It can fire beams from its tip and acts as a focus for her magic.

348.content: The Keiga Family is an organization in the <Animal Realm(畜生界)> led by <Saki Kurokoma(全名:骊驹早鬼 简称:早鬼)> and a rival to <Yachie(八千慧)> and <Yuuma(尤魔)>'s organizations. They represent brute force.

349.content: The Kiketsu Family is an organization in the <Animal Realm(畜生界)> led by <Yachie Kicchou(全名:吉吊八千慧 简称:八千慧)> and a rival to <Saki(骊驹早鬼)> and <Yuuma(尤魔)>'s organizations. They represent conniving and conspiring.

350.comment: Miyadeguchi, Mizuchi,宫出口,瑞灵,宫出口瑞灵
350.content: <Mizuchi Miyadeguchi(全名:宫出口瑞灵)> is a vengeful spirit. She can possess anyone regardless of strength. Mizuchi lives in Hell but roams Gensokyo in search of victims. She collects magical trinkets, and stalks <Reimu(灵梦)> to cause her trouble. Mizuchi has dark blue eyes and dark blue hair that fades to deep green in a ponytail, with two short braids to the sides and hairpins shaped like bundles of little <ghosts(亡灵)>. Mizuchi wears a black and white striped shirt and skirt over a short black dress. Mizuchi's legs stop at the thighs and dissipate into bluish mist. Her gloves have handcuffs with broken chains. Mizuchi has a very large handcuff around her neck, and uses the opposite cuff to catch possession victims.
